title: impossible chicken 'n broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw; drain.
Mix broccoli, cheese (2 cups), chicken and onion in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes. Knife should come out clean when inserted in middle.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until melted, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix well, pour into pan, then place in refrigerator.

title: asparagus with dill sauce
directions: Wash asparagus and trim tough ends.
Steam for 4 to 5 minutes until barely tender.
Drain.
Mix sauce ingredients in a cup and pour over asparagus.
Stir and warm over low heat for 2 minutes. Makes 3 servings.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger together with onions and celery. Cook 3/4 c. of rice.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pecan delights
directions: Beat egg white and sugar together until smooth and stands in peaks.
Add pecans; stir until mixed.
Drop by teaspoon in small amounts on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: herb bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour; combine 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, cheese and herbs.
Heat water and 4 tablespoons margarine until hot to touch, 125°.
Stir into dry mixture.
Stir in egg and only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth on lightly floured surface, about 4 minutes.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Roll into 12-inch square on floured surface.
Brush with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Cut in 25 squares; overlap square margarine side down in greased 12 cup tube pan.
Cover; rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until done.
Remove to wire rack.
Serve warm.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Add eggs, sugar and shortening together and mix.
Add buttermilk, then flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add flavoring.
Then stir soda and water together and pour in bowl, then mix together.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Cream together the shortening and brown sugar.
Beat the egg and add to mixture.
Add pecans, vanilla, salt and flour sifted with baking powder.
Spread evenly in an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into sticks.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients until zucchini is evenly coated.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Take filling out of cookies and make fine crumbs. Mix cream cheese and margarine. Add powdered sugar, pudding and milk. When thickens, fold in Cool Whip. Layer, starting with cookie crumbs.

title: oatmeal cookies (1)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each. Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon. Add alternately with milk. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts. Drop by Tbsp. on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Then put in and fold in one can drained (6 ounce) baby shrimp.
Form in a ball in aluminum paper. Put in freezer and take out 2 hours before serving.
Can be stored in freezer 2 weeks.
Serve with crackers.

title: 7-layered salad
directions: Layer the first 7 ingredients in salad bowl in order given. Spread mayonnaise or salad dressing to cover.
Sprinkle sugar and Parmesan cheese to taste.
Top with crumbled bacon and chopped eggs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving and add diced tomatoes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix
together
everything
except
chips and oleo.
Pour into 9
x 13-inch casserole.
Melt oleo and mix with chips and spread over
potato mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	until tender and drain. Cook rice until tender and
drain.
Mix
soup
and
sour
cream.
Add rice and chicken mixture.
Add
to
broccoli
in casserole dish.
Melt butter and add bread crumbs. Stir until well mixed. Add grated or sliced cheese
to	casserole
dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Heat in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place 12 paper muffin cups in muffin tins.
Fill cups with cranberry mixture.
Freeze.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: mary-mac's honey baked onion
directions: Peel and trim onions.
Cut in half and place in buttered baking pan.
Mix other ingredients; pour over onions.
Bake one hour at 325° or until soft.

title: eagle brand pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in pan; cook until thick.
Remove. Stir in 1/2 of nuts.
Put in pie shell.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip and nuts on top.
Serves 1 pie.

title: cocoa-cornflake macaroons *
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add cocoa, sugar and salt.
Stir good.
Add cornflakes and coconut.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 or 15 minutes.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients, then soak lean strips in marinade overnight.
Dry on lowest setting in oven with door cracked open for about 6 hours.
I hang the meat by toothpicks or in a dehydrator on 425° until dry.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Saute onions in margarine or butter until soft.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Cut in 5 tablespoons margarine.
Mix egg and milk together and add to dry ingredients. Stir until just moistened.
Add onions and 1/2 cup of the cheese. Spread batter in greased 8 or 9-inch pans.
Combine remaining cheese with poppy or celery seed.
Sprinkle over top of batter in pans.
Drizzle melted butter on top and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot.
This is excellent served with chili.

title: chili con carne skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat.
Add soup, chili powder and beans.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: no-bake peanut butter squares
directions: Melt Karo and brown sugar together in microwave just a little. Add peanut butter and stir.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated.
Press mixture into a 9 x 11-inch pan and refrigerate approximately 1 hour or proceed as follows.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces.
Place in boiling water just until color changes.
Do not cook tender.
Drain.
Place cabbage into baking dish.
Melt margarine.
Add flour until well mixed. Add milk.
Cook until thick.
If too thick, add more milk.
Add cheese and other ingredients.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over cabbage.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until browned at 350°.

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Saute onions with butter until tender.
In a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole mix in onions.
Stir in broccoli, noodles, cheese, pepper and mushrooms.
Combine crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Bake covered for 15 minutes, then take cover off.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: crab imperial
directions: Put crab in casserole. Combine mayo and cream. Add to crab. Mix well. Crab mixture should be quite moist. Add more mayo and cream if it isn't. Add eggs and Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Mix.
Can put bread crumbs on top if you want. Bake at 350° until thickened (about 15 minutes).

title: complete breakfast(beth's brunch)
directions: Remove crusts from 12 slices of Pepperidge Farm bread.
Place 6 slices in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Spread mayonnaise on each slice and then layer on the ham and cheese. Cover with the remaining 6 slices and butter the tops.
Mix the eggs, milk and dry mustard and pour over the sandwiches. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake until brown in a preheated 325° oven.
Let set for a minute before serving.

title: simple spaghetti
directions: Brown meat.
Add all but spaghetti and bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti.
Cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add about 1 c. Velveeta cheese.
Also very good reheated!

title: jalapeno and pimiento squares
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Spread mixture in a light greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; let stand 10 minutes. Cut into squares and serve immediately. Yields 3 dozen.

title: hawaiian cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve on gingersnaps or crackers.
Makes 3 1/4 cups.

title: honey's secret salad dressing
directions: Into blender container put:
sugar, paprika, salt, garlic, vinegar, and lime juice.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.
In a 2 c. measuring cup, pour oil and catsup.
Add this slowly to the blender and blend after each addition.
You may have to stop the blending process and stir from the bottom several times.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Place all ingredients into crock-pot. There is no need to brown meat first. Cover and cook for several hours. Add cubed potatoes (4 or 5) last hour (I put mine in sooner). Add more liquid, if needed. Peek and stir occasionally (but not necessary). You'll love this stew!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
(Note:
brown in the olive oil.)
Chop onion, green peppers and mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients and cook in a slow cooker for 6 to 8 hours.

title: frosting supreme
directions: Combine milk and cornstarch in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Remove mixture from heat and cool.
Combine sugar, shortening, butter, vanilla, lemon extract and salt.
Add cornstarch mixture and cream until smooth. Frosts two 9 inch layers.
Excellent on angel food cake.

title: rice onion casserole
directions: Stir the ingredients and cover good in oleo, then pour beef consomme and onion soup into oblong Pyrex dish.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Cover with lid.

title: ron's veggie dip
directions: Stir together and serve with raw veggies, such as carrot, celery, zucchini strips and broccoli or cauliflower florets.

title: lemon bites
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat 3/4 of mixture into bottom of 9 X 13 pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Strip meat from bone and save broth. Saute onion, celery, mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and drain.
Add water chestnuts, olives and pimentos to sauteed mixture and add spaghetti.
Add soups and milk.
Stir well.
Pour mixture into two 9 x 13-inch baking dishes.
Top each dish with 8 ounces cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
One pan can be frozen, just omit cheese and cover.

title: amaretto mousse trifle
directions: Sprinkle cake cubes evenly with Amaretto.
In small bowl, combine milk and pudding mix.
Beat at low speed 1 to 2 minutes. Let pudding stand 5 minutes to thicken.
Fold 1 1/2 cups of the whipped cream into pudding.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put sliced apples into a casserole dish. Pour sugar, flour and cinnamon mixture over the apples.

title: pioneer pie crust for cobblers
directions: Put Crisco in a mixing bowl.
Do not cream Crisco.
Add flour and salt and blend together (best to use fingers to blend it).
Add small amount ice water and mix.
Keep adding ice water until dough sticks together.
Roll dough out on a floured board with a floured rolling pin.
Do not handle dough too much, as it makes crust tough.
See separate page for cobblers pie fillings.
Dough makes enough for a 2-crust pie or cobbler.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together. Melt 1 cube butter in 9 x 12 baking pan. Pour batter over top. Add fruit. One of our favorites is peaches (fresh peaches with sugar to taste or canned less the juice; blueberries are good, too.) Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. This simple recipe is a really scrumptious dessert.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Boil water and sugar until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to boil.
Cool syrup.
Cover and chill.
Mix ice water, syrup and fruit juices.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 100.

title: wonderful spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with bread, crackers and/or vegetables for dipping.

title: tropical pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and chill until stiff.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mama's recipe for pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. This is good, tastes a lot like sweet potato pie to me.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: In a very large bowl, mix cereal, sugar, flour, salt and soda. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
May be used at once or covered and stored in refrigerator to use as needed.
Fill greased or lined muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Good to add chopped nuts or additional fruit (like blueberries).

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Melt oleo and cream cheese.
Add green chilies and juice. Drain 2 of the cans of corn; add the other entire can.
Heat until all is mixed and hot.
Will keep up to 3 weeks in refrigerator. (Children love this creamy corn.)

title: tuna rice roll
directions: Prepare rice by directions on box. Turn into bowl and cool slightly. Add tuna and 1/3 cup of soup. Prepare pie crust mix. Roll out to 14 x 11-inches. Spoon tuna mixture down center of pie crust. Bring sides up and over tuna to meet. Pinch together and fold ends under to enclose rice. Ease carefully onto cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Heat remaining soup to boiling. Remove and stir in sour cream. Serve over slices of tuna roll. Serves 6.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, spices and salt; work in shortening until crumbly.
Combine molasses, egg yolk and soda dissolved in boiling water.
Alternate layers of crumb mixture and egg mixture in pastry shell; top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 450° until crust edges start to brown.
Reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes or until firm.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Put egg whites aside.
Mix eggs (yellows), sugar, flour, butter, salt and vinegar together.
Mix egg whites with mixer, then add to the other mixture gradually.
Put in a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake until done, about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 30 minute ribs
directions: Place ribs in large pot.
Add enough cold water to cover ribs completely; cover with lid.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Drain.
Grill ribs on medium heat for 10 minutes or until ribs are cooked through, turning occasionally and brushing generously with barbecue sauce. Makes 3 servings.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and whipped
(4 ounce) topping.
Spread over cooled cake.
Mix pudding and milk until smooth and thick.
Pour over cooled base.
Top with 4 ounces whipped topping and sprinkle with grated chocolate bar.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray an 8 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Add rice.
Mix cans of soup in separate bowl.
Add half of this mixture to rice in pan. Put chicken pieces on and cover with remaining soup mixture. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 5.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a Dutch oven or roaster.
Bake at 250°, covered, for 5 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a straight sided glass bowl, layer spinach in bottom. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Crumble bacon over spinach and add a layer of onion slices.
Cover with a layer of iceberg lettuce.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover with a layer of frozen peas, then a layer of hard-boiled eggs.
Cover with thick layer of mayonnaise, being careful to seal the edges. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cloud nine dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
With an electric mixer, cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add orange peel, ginger and marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Serve with assorted fresh fruit slices.
Great with strawberries also.

title: ham party rolls
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Place the minced ham over the four packs of rolls.
Sprinkle the grated cheese over the ham.
Put the top half of the rolls on this.
Saute the onion in margarine and add mustard and Worcestershire.
Brush this mixture on roll tops.
Put in a 350° oven and bake until thoroughly heated and cheese is bubbly.
Cut apart and serve.
These party rolls freeze beautifully if wrapped airtight.
They can be taken directly from freezer to oven.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon extract.
Add flour and 7-Up alternately, beating after each addition.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Put all juices together in 2 large punch bowls (1/2 in each). Do not add ginger ale until seconds before serving.
Make ice rings with maraschino cherries in to float on top of punch.
Use some crushed ice to make and to keep juices cold.

title: crock-pot enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and ground beef in a skillet until meat is brown; drain.
Put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients, except Doritos.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Ten minutes before serving, add Doritos to mixture and stir.
A great dish with just a little effort!

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix together well.
Form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Freeze.
Cook as desired or needed.
Bake at 350° about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: ham and potato bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add potatoes and ham to cheese sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: rhubarb jam spread
directions: Cook rhubarb and sugar (on low heat and keep stirring) for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple and juice.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in strawberry jello.
Stir until jello is completely dissolved.
Chill before serving.
This can be frozen or canned.

title: chestnut dressing(turkey)
directions: Make two 1/2-inch slits with a sharp knife in the shell of each chestnut.
Place them in a deep saucepan with the oil and cook slowly for 5 minutes, shaking the pan frequently.
Then bake in a very hot oven (400°) for 5 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Peel nuts and mash the nuts and add to the bread crumbs which have been blended with all the ingredients.
Stuff turkey lightly.

title: lumpia shanghai
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Add egg and soy sauce; mix thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper.
At one end of a lumpia wrapper, spoon about 2 tablespoons of pork mixture and roll tightly.
Brush one end of wrapper with water to seal.
Cut roll into 2-inch pieces.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with hot sweet and sour sauce.

title: cooked minute fudge icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from fire.
Beat until creamy, enough to spread.
Cover one 9-inch layer cake.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Save 1 cup of strawberries for the top.
Line dish with a layer of vanilla wafer crumbs.
Mix powdered sugar, melted butter, beaten eggs and 1 teaspoon of vanilla; layer on crumbs.
Add a layer of sliced berries.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Using a coarse blade, grind onions, cabbage, tomatoes and peppers.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with pickling salt and let stand overnight. Rinse and drain well. Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric. Pour over vegetables.
Heat over medium heat until vegetables are transparent.
Pour into sterilized jar and process in hot water bath 10 minutes.

title: whipped cream cheese potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes and add all remaining ingredients.
Put in lightly buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken rice italian
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove excess fat from chicken.
Season with salt and oregano.
Remove and reserve 1/4 cup tomato sauce. Combine remaining sauce, rice, zucchini, water and salt in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir well.
Arrange chicken over rice mixture.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour.
Spoon reserved sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Make flour, butter and powdered sugar like a pie crust.
Bake at 325° until light brown.
Let cool.
Mix well cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add Cool Whip.
Top with strawberries and Danish Dessert Glaze and Pie Filling.

title: barbecue turkey
directions: Prepare and cook the turkey as for roasted turkey up to the last hour of baking time.
Mix the other ingredients together to make a barbecue sauce.
During the last hour of roasting, baste the turkey frequently with the sauce, omitting the use of foil. Serves about 12 to 15.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Prepare onions as directed; cut into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Heat oil (1-inch) in 3-quart saucepan to 375°.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand beater until smooth. Dip each ring into batter, letting excess drip into bowl.
Fry a few onions at a time in hot oil, turning once, until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cut the meat into strips and the mushrooms into thin slices. Brown the meat in butter in a frying pan. Pour the cognac over the meat and flamb. Add salt and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Return to the heat. Add the mushrooms, the Worcestershire sauce, the ketchup and the fresh cream. Stir well and leave uncovered on a low heat for 5 minutes, not more. Serve with rice.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine and 1 square chocolate.
Blend sugar, vanilla, eggs, crumbs, coconut and nuts into margarine-chocolate mixture.
Mix well and press into ungreased 11 x 7-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix by package directions. Pour 2 cups batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels and margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.
Spread caramel over cake; spread remaining cake batter over caramel.
Top with nuts (optional).
Bake for 30 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp, remove from pan, drain and crumble.
Add 1/2 c. of bacon fat left in the pan.
Add flour and onion.
Stir in spices.
Cook only until medium thickness.
Add potatoes, parsley and crumbled bacon.
Mix carefully with 2 forks to prevent mashing the potatoes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on cookie sheet and seal perforations. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and dressing.
Spread on dough.
Top with vegetables, saving cream for last topping.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Mix together sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Pour over vegetables.
Store in airtight bowl.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes, potato chips or bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk; add crushed crackers or wafers and mix well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Press in container or make into rolls on wax paper.
Slice when well chilled.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: mock margarita punch
directions: In 4-quart nonmetal container, combine lemonade, lime-ade, powdered sugar and crushed ice; mix well.
Cover and freeze, stirring occasionally.
Remove container from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Spoon 2 cups slush mixture into blender; add 1 cup club soda; blend until frothy.

title: potato latkes(pancakes)
directions: Put eggs, onion, salt, pepper, flour, baking powder and 1/2 cup of the potato cubes into blender container.
Process at grate until potatoes have gone through the blades.
Stop blender and add remaining potatoes.
Cover and process at chop just until all potato cubes have passed through the blades.
Use a rubber spatula to help guide potatoes into the blades.
Do not overblend.
Pour onto a hot, well-greased griddle.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield:
12 pancakes.
Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: peanut butter fluff sandwich
directions: Take some bread.
Get the jar of peanut butter and fluff. Take the lids off.
Then you take a knife, stick the knife into the peanut butter and pull it out and spread it on the bread. Then you stick the knife in the fluff and pull it out and spread it on the bread.
Then you take the other bread and slap it down on the other piece of bread and then you eat it.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix both puddings and milk until thickened, then spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with the rest of Cool Whip and chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.
You may sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: pesto salad
directions: Gently take leaves off of basil stalk and tear into smaller pieces.
Add basil, oil, nuts, garlic and salt to blender.
Blend until relatively smooth.
Add Parmesan, Romano and butter and blend slightly.
Pour over cooked tortellini and mix well.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375.
In large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes until beef is thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently.
Drain.
Stir in pasta sauce; cook until thoroughly heated.
In medium bowl, combine mozzarella cheese and sour cream; mix well.
Pour hot beef mixture into ungreased 9.5 or 10 inch glass deep-dish pie pan or 11 X 7 inch glass baking dish. Spoon cheese mixture over beef mixture. Unroll dough over cheese mixture.
If using pie pan, separate dough into 8 triangles; arrange points toward center over cheese mixture, crimping outside edges if necessary.
In small bowl, mix parmesan cheese and margarine, spread evenly over dough.
Bake at 375 for 18 to 25 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased dish; bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream soft butter, sugar, salt and egg thoroughly.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add flour. Put in cookie press. Press out designs on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 400° oven for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch pan with no stick cooking spray (2 or 3 sprays).
Spread on bottom and sides of pan with paper towel. Put gelatin and water in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve completely.

title: cranberry macadamia bark
directions: Melt coating in a saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring until smooth. Add nuts and cranberries; mix well. Spread onto a foil-lined baking sheet. Cool. Break into pieces. Yield: 1 1/4 pounds.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in shortening until soft.
Cook the rice and broccoli separately.
Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf in clay pot
directions: Soak clay pot in cold water for 20 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Form into loaf and place in ovensafe casserole.
Lay green peppers, carrots and potatoes around meat loaf.
Pour a little catsup on top of meat loaf.
Put in cold oven, then turn oven to 425° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green beans greek style
directions: Prepare green beans.
Saute onion in the oil.
Add tomatoes; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add green beans, seasoning and a few teaspoons water.
Cover; cook on low heat until beans are tender.

title: spiced almonds
directions: Combine the cumin, cayenne, salt and sugar and mix.
Saute nuts in 1/2 cup sugar in oil over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes until caramelized.
Drain excess oil.
Put in separate bowl and mix with spice mixture. (Break apart as you go and be careful they're still quite hot.)
When cooler, separate as much as you can and try not to eat them all!

title: easy sauerkraut-frank dinner
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rinse sauerkraut and press out liquid. Heat margarine in saucepan and stir in onion and apples.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Toss with caraway and sauerkraut.
Place in 2-quart greased baking dish.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes.
Cook franks until plump, then split in half.
Place franks on top of casserole and top with cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: no fail divinity
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Candy thermometer should read 260°.
If not, cook 2 minutes longer.

title: cucumber apple rings
directions: Use large cucumbers, even if they are turning yellow. Peel and slice 1/2 inch thick and remove seeds. Combine cucumbers, lime and water. Soak for 24 hours; drain and wash well. Cover with ice water and soak for 3 hours.

Important to drain well. Add 1 cup vinegar, 1 tablespoon alum and 2 bottles food coloring. Add enough water to cover cucumbers. Put on stove and simmer (do not boil) for 2 hours. Drain and throw away water.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat candies and milk in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently, until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in margarine with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press half of the crumbly mixture in pan and bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drizzle with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbly mixture over top.

title: mock eggs benedict
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour. Add milk gradually. Cook until bubbly, plus 1 minute longer, stirring constantly. Add ham and cheese to sauce.
Cook until heated through. Carefully blend in eggs, stirring gently.
Season with salt and pepper. Serve over toast or fresh baked biscuits.

title: raisin pie
directions: Bake at slow temperature (250°).
If you use bought pie shells, cook crust before putting filling in crust, but just partially.

title: light pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: biscuit mix(for saturday morning biscuits)
directions: Blend; knead 10 strokes.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Begin with and end with flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Glaze while cake is hot (do not use self-rising flour).

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil; add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Yields 8 servings.

title: patio chicken
directions: Spread dry onion soup mix evenly on bottom of baking dish. Cover with raw rice.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Combine soup and water; pour over chicken.
Scatter mushrooms and pimiento over top.
Season with pepper and salt.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: maple sauce(dessert sauce)
directions: Add the water to the maple sugar and boil until it reaches the thread stage.
Add the walnut meats.

title: mock barbecued chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
In electric or regular frying pan, combine all ingredients, then add chicken.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, turning to brown evenly.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes, or until tender.
Remove to platter.
Skim off oil.
Add a little water and stir to loosen brownings.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well. In a small bowl, mix the brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Pour 1/2 of batter in 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle 1/2 sugar mixture over top. Repeat. Swirl with knife. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seafood fettuccini
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Heat butter and garlic in skillet over medium heat until lightly browned.
Add crab, half and half and pepper.
Heat about 3 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese; stir for 1 minute.
Toss Crab Delight sauce with noodles and serve.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: stacked tortillas
directions: On your
plate, place 1 tortilla and put about 2 tablespoons of hot
chili con carne on top.
Spread evenly (you can put as much
as
you
wish).
Sprinkle some chopped onion and cheese next.
Put
another
tortilla
on
top
and
repeat the process. On the
last
layer,
you
can top this with a fried egg, if you want.
Put
a
dash or two of Louisiana hot sauce over it all.

title: creamy crab and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In medium mixing bowl, blend together cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients and place mixture in glass pie plate. Bake, uncovered, for 15 to 18 minutes until heated through and lightly browned. (Pine nuts can be sprinkled on top before baking.) Serve with toasted wedges of gourmet bread or thin crust Boboli.

title: leek soup
directions: Cook bacon in a Dutch oven over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add leeks.
Saute 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add water; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Add bouillon cubes, potatoes and basil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in milk and cook until thoroughly heated.
Yield: 7 cups.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together. Add salad dressing mix and shrimp. Chill before serving. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: carrots in cranberry sauce
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, melt butter for about 2 minutes in a microwave oven.
Add cranberry sauce and cook for about 2 minutes, until cranberry sauce is melted.
Stir once or twice while cooking.
Add cooked, drained carrots and toss together gently to coat carrots.
If desired, add salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp party sandwiches
directions: Combine shrimp, lemon juice, butter, chili sauce, chopped egg whites and cream cheese.
Cut bread into desired sizes and shapes. Spread with shrimp mixture and garnish with grated egg yolk. Diamond shapes are suggested for bread.

title: microwave pot roast and vegetables
directions: Place roast in 4-quart casserole.
Rub with salt and pepper. Sprinkle flour around roast in dish and add water.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High 10 to 15 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn and microwave at Medium-low for 45 to 50 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and onion.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave at Medium-high for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mash avocados, but not so that they are pureed.
Add other ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Do not use blender.

title: catfish nuggets
directions: Cut fillets into 1-inch cubes; set aside.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, sesame seed, salt and pepper in a small bowl; set aside.
Dip fish cubes in butter; roll in cracker crumb mixture. Place fish cubes 1/2-inch apart on aluminum foil lined baking sheets.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish is golden brown.
Serve immediately with your favorite dip for fish or with Sour Cream Bleu Cheese Dip.
Yield:
6 dozen appetizers.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Boil 11 cups water with salt.
Let cool; pour over cucumbers. Let set for 2 weeks.
Drain and wash.
Add 2 tablespoons alum and water to cover.
Let set for 24 hours.
Drain and cover with vinegar and 2 tablespoons pickling spices (be sure to put spices in cloth).
Let set for 24 hours.
Drain through strainer; put spices back in jar.
Add 3 cups sugar each day for 3 days (9 cups sugar in all).
You may refrigerate and use from gallon jar or seal in smaller jars.
Be sure juice covers pickles and jars must be hot in order for them to seal.

title: fried sweet puffs bunuelos
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add butter; with fingers mix until mixture is coarse. Mix eggs with milk and add to mixture.
Stir until soft solid dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth. Shape into balls slightly larger than marbles.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll each ball out into a thin circle; cut center out with thimble.
Deep fry until puffy and brown on both sides. Drain on paper towels.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon and serve. Makes 5 dozen.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Blend broth, soup and steak sauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except the Parmesan cheese.
Put in a shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tahitian delight salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain pineapple and save liquid and add 3/4 cup water.
Add to Jell-O.
Chill until very thick, then fold in fruit and coconut.
Chill.

title: party mix
directions: Combine over low heat.
Mix all ingredients in roasting pan. Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours, stirring and turning carefully with wooden spoon every 15 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix cubed bread with 5 cups milk. Let stand at least an hour, mixing from time to time. Add butter, raisins and apples to bread mixture; set aside. Beat eggs, vanilla, sugars and cinnamon. Add rest of milk (1 cup) to egg mixture, mixing well. Add to bread mixture. Stir well. Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan. Bake on top shelf of oven. Check in 1 hour to see if center is puffed up and top is brown. If not, bake in 15 minute increments until done. May need another 1/2 hour. After cooled, sift top with powdered sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and onion together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Mix melted butter, soup and sour cream together.
Add to potatoes. Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place sliced Velveeta cheese over this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix together wet ingredients.
Stir just until combined.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Top with topping.

title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce in pieces and make a layer in size dish you want to use. Add a layer of each ingredient (except eggs) as listed and repeat. Top with sliced eggs. Nice and crunchy.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and
eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk. Add
sifted
dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix in jam.
Pour into three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour cream into a medium size bowl (do not whip cream).
Slowly stir in flour and mix well.
Turn onto floured surface and knead.
Roll out and cut.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pizza casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook beef and onions until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato paste, chopped tomatoes and Spatini.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and add to mixture.
Pour in 2-quart greased casserole dish and top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in cottage cheese and whipped topping.
Store in refrigerator until firm.
May be molded.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
If using noodles that have to be cooked, cook only until half done.
Drain.
Mix together the drained beef, tomatoes and spaghetti sauce.
Spread 1 1/2 cups in bottom of deep baking dish.
Lay 3 of the noodles on sauce.
Then spread some more sauce and 1/2 of the cottage cheese.
Make another layer of noodles, meat sauce and cottage cheese.
Then add rest of tomato sauce.
Spread Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake, covered with foil, for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and continue to bake until cheese is lightly browned.

title: chicken soup
directions: Saute onion in a 6-quart pot over medium heat until golden brown.
Add the next 4 ingredients and cook for 3 minutes.
Then add the next 5 ingredients and cook 3 minutes.
Add broth and cook 20 minutes, or until potatoes are done.
Then add chicken and hoisin sauce, cooked 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: country biscuits and chicken
directions: Grease 8 x 12-inch dish; combine first 4 ingredients and 1 cup of cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour over casserole. Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine Bisquick, milk and 1/2 can French fried onion rings; mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonful to form 6 biscuits around edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Top with remaining cheese and French fried onion rings and bake 2 to 3 minutes until onions are toasted.

title: orange chiffon pie(for diabetics)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin and sweetener in water.
Add orange juice.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until thickened, but not set.
Beat on high for 3 minutes or until foamy.
Fold in Cool Whip until completely combined.
Pour into crust.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: peanut butter cup pie
directions: Mix dessert crust mix with 3 tablespoons cream and 2 tablespoons water.
Press mixture into 9-inch pie pan and freeze until firm, about 15 minutes.
With mixer on high speed, beat remaining cream until soft peaks form; refrigerate.
In bowl with mixer at low speed, beat milk with contents of filling mix and peanut butter packet 30 seconds.
Increase speed to high and beat 3 minutes.
Spread 1 cup mix on crust.
Warm topping pouch according to package directions.
Spread over mixture in pan and spread 1/4 to 1/2 cup of candy quarters over topping.
Fold 3 cups reserved cream into remaining peanut butter mixture.
Spread over candy.
Refrigerate until firm, about 45 minutes.
Spoon remaining cream in dollops on pie.
Garnish with remaining candy.
Makes 12 servings.

title: bob hall's oatmeal scones
directions: *Health choice ingredients listed first.

title: cheese cake
directions: Prepare Graham Cracker Crust in 13 x 9-inch pan. (Double Graham Cracker Crust recipe.) Place Pet milk in freezer for 3 hours. Prepare lemon jello with hot water; set aside.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and lemon juice. Beat milk until fairly thick. Add cheese mixture to jello, then fold in the Pet milk. Pour over Graham Cracker Crust. Chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to banana mix.
Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add flour mixture gradually.
Place batter in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: walnut holiday cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, beaten in one at a time.
Sift together flour and baking powder and stir into mixture. Separately mix cherries and walnuts.
Fold into batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.
Great for brunch.
Delicious and moist.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add milk, nuts and vanilla and cook 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered dish and chill until firm enough to cut.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add all other ingredients except Cheez Whiz. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Add Cheez Whiz and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: clam dip
directions: Rub mixing bowl with garlic.
Gradually blend lemon juice into remaining ingredients.
Mix with electric blender until well blended.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Place broccoli package on paper towel in microwave. Cook on High 6 minutes.
Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into skillet or pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Let cool and add red food coloring and fresh strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: white squash casserole
directions: Grate squash on coarse grater.
Grate onion on medium grater. Mix all ingredients together to the consistency of custard.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make instant pudding.
Put aside and allow to gel.
Slice pound cake.

Layer ingredients in punch bowl in following order: pound cake, strawberries with some juice, crushed pineapple with some juice, spoon some pudding over the pineapple and place banana slices over pudding.
Continue making layers until within 2 to 3 inches of top of bowl.
Fill in top space with Cool Whip.
Garnish with sliced cherries and pecan halves.

title: mushroom rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour in covered casserole dish.

title: sister's pea salad
directions: Drain and rinse chestnuts very well; cut small and marinate overnight or at least 8 hours in mixture of salad oil, vinegar and sugar.
Later, drain chestnuts very well.
Drain peas very well. Mix ingredients well and chill.
Serve plain as vegetable or on lettuce as salad, or in tomato halves, shells or slices.
Keeps for 1 week.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together ingredients and form balls.
Roll in flour. Brown in a skillet with shortening.
Place in casserole dish and pour over 1 can mushroom soup with 3/4 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tangy green beans
directions: Combine lemon juice, sugar, butter, cornstarch, cloves, apple and onion in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce comes to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until apple and onion are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add beans; heat through.
Sprinkle with toasted, sliced almonds, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: pistachio pudding pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 Cool Whip together.
Mix pudding mix according to package directions.
Put cream cheese mixture on crust, next pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Grate a Hershey almond candy bar over top.
Chill.

title: foolproof cheese souffle
directions: Combine in top of double boiler the Minute tapioca, milk and salt over boiling water and bring to a scalding point (3 to 5 minutes).
Cook 5 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Add grated cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and boiling water. Cool slightly.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Turn into greased casserole dish, placed in pan of hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: quick fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk together for 5 minutes.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Beat very little.
Put in a buttered dish.

title: reuben pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper; let harden. Refrigerate.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Combine milk and next 7 ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken fricassee with dumplings
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Mix baking mix, salt, paprika and pepper in paper or plastic bag.
Shake 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time to coat thoroughly.
Melt shortening and butter in large skillet; brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken.
Drain fat from skillet; stir in soup and milk and add chicken.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until thickest pieces are tender.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice the cucumbers 1/4-inch thick. Slice onions 1/8-inch thick. Place both in a large non-metallic bowl. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over cucumbers and onions. Stir well for 5 minutes. Cover and refrigerate 3 hours before serving. Store in the refrigerator for up to 3 months, stirring occasionally. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: pesto cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rub 1 tablespoon butter over bottom and sides of 9-inch diameter spring-form pan.
Mix bread crumbs with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Coat pan with crumb mixture.

title: stir-fried shrimp and pea pods
directions: Blanch pea pods in boiling salted water for 1 minute.
Drain and set aside.
Heat wok, add the peanut oil and stir-fry shrimp for 30 seconds.
Add pea pods, dry white wine, lemon juice, soy sauce, salt and pepper and toss together until heated through. Adjust seasoning and garnish with parsley.
Serve immediately with boiled rice.

title: aunt nancy's lemon chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Dip in lemon juice, then flour. Lightly brown chicken in a little oil in a frying pan.
Cover chicken with the water, bouillon and brown sugar mixture and cook until done.
The liquid will become thick so you may have to add more as it is cooking.

title: best fluffy pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl. Set aside.
Stir together milk, melted butter and egg yolks.
Whip egg whites.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture and fold in egg whites.
Batter should hold its shape, but not be too stiff.
Bake on heated griddle.
Serve immediately with favorite topping.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown the meat and drain.
Add beans and garlic.
Place 4 noodles in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half of meat mixture over noodles.
Top with 4 more noodles.
Spread remaining meat mixture over noodles.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Combine water and salsa.
Pour over noodles.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Combine sour cream, onions and cheese.
Spoon over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for about 5 more minutes.
For easier serving, let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Spread mixture into 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: In large bowl, blend all ingredients together.
Spoon into 2 glass pie plates (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.
Yield: 2 pies.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla; cream.
Add flour, chips and nuts; mix together.
Drop by scant teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Wet fork and press down each cookie.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Combine ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cover and simmer approximately 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yummy with biscuits.

title: chocolate decadence
directions: In large glass bowl, tear 1/2 of the cake into chunks and cover bottom of bowl.
Spoon 1/2 of the pudding over the cake. Spoon 1/2 of the Cool Whip over cake and pudding.
Sprinkle 1/2 of crushed Skor or Heath bars over Cool Whip.
Repeat steps.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: raspberry cordial
directions: Crush raspberries and mix with vodka and other ingredients. Let stand in unrefrigerated jar (tightly sealed) for 10 days. Shake once in a while.
Strain small amounts through damp cheesecloth, pressing berries to extract juice.
Strain again through 3 layers of cheesecloth.
Add light corn syrup to taste. Store on a shelf in an airtight bottle or jar.
It keeps for months.
A nice hostess gift.

title: chili rice
directions: Stir chili, tomatoes, onions and garlic powder in a large skillet; bring to a bowl.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Melt chocolate squares and margarine.
Beat eggs, sugar, peppermint extract, flour and salt.
Add melted chocolate mixture and 1 cup nuts, if desired.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: In a large saucepan warm the olive oil and butter together over medium heat.

When the butter has melted, add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until wilted, 3 to 4 minutes.	Stir in the garlic and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer, stirring frequently and stopping before the onion and garlic brown.
Sprinkle the flour and continue cooking, stirring continuously, until the mixture turns a golden-blond color, 10 to 15 minutes.
Then, whisking continuously, slowly pour in the stock until it is smoothly incorporated.
When the mixture begins to simmer, stir in the cream.	Let it return to the simmer.
Remove from the heat and add the Parmesan, chicken base or bouillon cubes, lemon juice and sugar and stir until thoroughly blended.

Add the sour cream, spinach, artichoke bottoms, Monterey Jack cheese and hot sauce and then stir until the ingredients are thoroughly combined and the cheese has melted.	Transfer to a warmed serving bowl and serve immediately with toasted pita chips that have been cut into wedges.
Makes 8 to 10 appetizers.

title: ham and swiss quiche
directions: Place ham in bottom of unbaked pie shell; pack down lightly. Top with Swiss cheese.
Beat together eggs, onion, mustard and salt.
Gradually stir in cream.
Pour over ham and cheese layers in pie shell.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over surface.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: sweet potato piedallas, texas
directions: Stir together and add to unbaked pie crust.
Pre-heat oven to 450°.
Cook 10 minutes.
Reduce heat in oven to 350° and cook for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli with sour cream
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add rest of the ingredients to make a smooth sauce.
Mix with broccoli and place in a baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Grate cheese over top.
Spinach may be used instead of broccoli.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Add all ingredients together except Swiss cheese. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish sprayed with Pam spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake additional 10 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over bottom.
Prepare cake mix according to directions; pour in pan.
Mix 2 sticks butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together; mix well and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until done.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut chicken wings and dip in Tabasco sauce.
Salt and pepper wings.
Put in hot grease until done.

title: cheesy crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients, except crab meat and cheese, for topping.
Fold in crab meat.
Put mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle top with additional cheese and bake for 5 minutes more.
Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: greek black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Marinate 6 to 8 hours.
Refrigerate, stirring occasionally.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Be sure egg whites are room temperature.
Beat the whites of 3 eggs with a dash of cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry. Gradually beat in 6 tablespoons of sugar, sprinkling a little at a time over the surface of egg whites.
Continue beating until very smooth and glossy.
Pile lightly on top of the pie filling which has been thoroughly cooled.
Seal the edge of the meringue over the pastry to prevent it from shrinking and leaving the edge as it browns.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Baking slowly allows each cell of the meringue to become firm and retain its height on the pie.
Makes enough for one 9-inch pie.

title: fat-free banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add wet ingredients.
Spray loaf pan. Add batter to pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Line a round baking dish with crust.
Pour in pie filling. Sprinkle with sugar and spices.
Dot with butter.
Cover with remaining pie crust.
Flute edges.
Slit crust.
Bake at 375° until top is brown.

title: brownie cake
directions: In saucepan, bring margarine, cocoa and water to boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour over remaining ingredients; beat until smooth. Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Spread in a large cake pan (13 x 9-inch).
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: missionary cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in large pan and boil for 2 minutes. Let mixture cool.
Add two teaspoons baking soda and 3 cups flour.
Layer or loaf.
Bake at 350°.
Powdered sugar icing may be used.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients with cooked potatoes, pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bridge sticks
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and pat in bottom of a pan; cook for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: mackenzie's green jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water. Add cream cheese. Whip into jello with mixer. Add 1 cup juice from fruit cocktail. Let set in refrigerator. Whip Dream Whip according to package directions. Refrigerate. When jello is set, whip with mixer the jello the Dream Whip. Add fruit. Chop extra cherries, squeezing the juice from them. Put into mold. Chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Place the black-eyed peas in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add cold water to cover.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15 minutes, or until just tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain again and place in a large bowl. Add the corn, carrots, celery, red peppers and onions to the bowl.
Sprinkle with the vinegar and toss well.
Allow to stand for at least 30 minutes at room temperature.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix according to directions; spread onto a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the cream cheese with 10 tablespoons pineapple juice until smooth. Spread over cookie.
Top with pineapple chunks and fresh or well drained canned fruit.

title: caesar cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrot, onion and green pepper together. Sprinkle sugar on top of shredded ingredients.
Do not stir.
Set aside.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Add onion; cook slightly.
Add catsup, salt, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Add pork and beans, kidney beans and lima beans.
Mix well.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: eggnog
directions: Whip the whites and yolks of 6 eggs into a stiff cream, adding sugar.
Pour into milk, adding brandy and a flavor of nutmeg. Stir up and thoroughly mix the ingredients and add the 3 additional egg whites, well whipped.

title: mommy's chicken breast supreme
directions: Add pepper to chicken breast.
Wrap slices of bacon around each halved chicken breast.
Place layer of dried beef in bottom of 13x9-inch casserole dish.
Arrange bacon wrapped chicken on beef slices.
Cover with mixture of soup, sour cream and cream cheese. Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 325 degrees until tender.
Remove foil and let brown lightly.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add flour and pecans.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown. Cool.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add shortening, bananas and egg.
Beat until smooth. Add oats; stir.
Use greased sheet pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: millionaire or turtle brownies
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Pour half the batter into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Mix milk with caramels and melt in double boiler.
Pour milk/caramel mixture over hot cake.
Mix nuts and chocolate chips.
Sprinkle half of this mixture over caramel layer.
Pour the rest of the cake batter on top.
Top this with remaining chips and nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together. Add eggs and buttermilk and then coconut. Add vanilla and mix well. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: italian torta(a-la-venito)
directions: Crush crackers fine; add lukewarm milk and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning in separate bowl, beat eggs well, adding sugar, vanilla and brandy.
Combine this with cracker mixture.
If thick, add small amount of milk to consistency of cake batter. Add fruit mix, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a well-greased pan.
Test middle of cake for doneness.
Remove from oven and when slightly cooled, sprinkle with sugar.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add the refried beans, oregano, cumin and garlic powder; heat through.
Place 3 noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish coated with Pam.
Cover with 1/2 of meat mixture. Repeat layers; top with remaining noodles.
Combine salsa and water; pour over noodles.
Cover; bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Spread with sour cream; sprinkle with olives and cheese.

title: nothing but crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and oil.
Mix well. Shape into 8 patties.
Coat with crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator for an hour.
Pan-fry in medium heat oil in skillet until brown on both sides.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: easy fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large micro-safe bowl on High for 1 minute.
Stir; micro for 1 to 2 more minutes until almost completely melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in 8-inch square pan lined with foil.
Refrigerate 2 hours until hard.

title: snowballs
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, salt and margarine.
Mix well. Add vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour.
Work nuts into dough. Chill well.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 - 10 minutes or until set but not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar immediately.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Store in airtight container.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Add egg, milk and butter, stirring only enough to dampen the flour.
Add the apples.
Stir only enough to blend (batter should not be smooth).
Spoon into muffin tins (use paper cups).
Fill each about 2/3 full.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Serves 12.

title: russian apple pie
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar for 3-4 minutes; add flour; mix well. Chop apples into small pieces and stir into mixture. Line pan with foil, cover well with cooking spray. Pour 1/2 mixture into pan; sprinkle cinnamon; add remaining batter; sprinkle with cinnamon again. Cook for 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Check with a knife or toothpick for doneness. (Make desirable decorations with fruit on top prior to baking.)

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave on High 15 to 20 seconds. Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: quebec meatball ragout
directions: Mix well 3 kinds of meat:
beef, pork and veal.
Add the onion, parsley, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and dry mustard.
Add the bread soaked in the milk and blend in with meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Make into balls.
Fry the meatballs in the butter or fat of your choice.
Pour 3 cups of water over the meatballs. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix together the flour and 1/2 cup of water.
Pour into the broth and continue cooking, stirring until it thickens to a good consistency.
Delicious over boiled potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs until blended.
Beat 1 minute. Stir in remaining ingredients except apples and nuts.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour in pan.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Simmer on low for about 2 hours. Serve with shredded cheese and sour cream.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions.
Drain and put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients. Stir.
Cover and cook on low temperature for 5 hours.

title: sausage and squash dressing
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet; add celery and onion, stir fry a few minutes.
Add squash and stir fry another minute.
In a large bowl, mix all the other ingredients until blended well.
Add sausage and squash mixture to this and mix well.
Pour into baking dish or baking pan and bake at 300-325 degrees until brown on top and as dry as you like your dressing.
Serve hot.

title: six bean easy soup
directions: Saute the ground sausage and onion in pan.
In large kettle, add the tomato soup, water, brown sugar, Tabasco sauce, ketchup, mustard, pork and beans and chili beans with sauce.
Drain the liquid from the kidney beans, butter beans, cut green beans and wax beans.
Add these beans to the other ingredients plus the ground sausage mixture.
Mix all together and let simmer for 1 hour or more.
Best if made ahead.

title: italian beef bake
directions: Cut meat in strips and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cut up tomatoes (save the juice) and put tomatoes, onion and pepper strips on top of the meat.
Mix the juice in cornstarch and steak sauce and pour over the top; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in two cups hot water and cool.
Drain pineapple and blueberries together.
Measure 1 3/4 cups juice from fruit and mix with jello.
Take out 3/4 cup of jello and juice and set aside.
Add blueberries, pineapple and nuts to jello; let jell.
Add the 3/4 cup reserved liquid to Cool Whip and spread on top.
This should be made in a 9 x 13-inch container.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: good and easy freezer pickles
directions: Mix together; pour over cucumbers and onion.
Let stand 3 hours.
Put in jars; screw caps and freeze.
(Leave 1/2 to 1-inch at top.)
Leave in freezer at least 24 hours.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Puree
berries.
Whisk oil and eggs together.
Sift dry ingredients
into a large bowl and make a well.
Add puree and eggs.
Mix	by
hand.
Bake
in
a	loaf pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: better than love cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, bake cake according to directions. Meanwhile in medium saucepan, combine pineapple with juice and sugar.
Cook over medium heat stirring occasionally until thick and syrupy.
When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce top with a fork at 1-inch intervals.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake and spread evenly.
Cool completely.
Combine pudding mix with milk.
Blend until thick.
Spread over cake.
Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta.
Meanwhile, place all chopped items in bowl; add vinegar, oil and garlic salt and mix.
Fold into cooked pasta. Refrigerate.
Add Feta cheese before serving.
May have to add more wine vinegar when tossing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cut broccoli into small flowerets. Combine broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon bits in serving dish. Just before serving, pour dressing over salad.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil and beat well.
Add eggs; beat. Then add milk, figs, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Take individual crescent roll.
Add pepperoni, sauce and cheese.
Roll up and slice into thick slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes. Serve with warm pizza sauce. Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: nancy and zula mae's pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Spoon in flour, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Fold in nuts.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Drop batter by 1/2 teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 200° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken with rice(method:  dutch oven)
directions: Brown chicken breasts in small amount of oil; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine undiluted soup and rice; spoon over top of browned chicken in Dutch oven.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top and cover.
Bake in hot coals for about 45 minutes, until done and liquid is absorbed.

title: ravioli
directions: Mix together until rather on the stiff side.
Knead dough well. Roll thin and cut in squares.

title: carrot slaw
directions: Clean and grate carrots.
Add raisins and drained crushed pineapple.
Add slaw dressing to taste.

title: pork chops and creamed corn
directions: Melt butter in skillet; then brown pork chops with the onion. Add creamed corn and milk in skillet.
Let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mash Velveeta cheese and add cream cheese, garlic and pecans. Make into rolls.
Roll in chili powder.
Wrap in plastic. Store in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: midwest chili tamale pie
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in soup, water, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat.
Prepare corn bread.
Spread chili mix in greased 10 x 6 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spread batter over chili mix.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: ann's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Blend in oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate flour and milk.
Add vanilla, lemon and baking powder.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or a little longer.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs about 5 minutes; add sugar gradually.
Then add pumpkin, lemon juice, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice and nutmeg. Blend together with mixer, then add flour.
Mix together well. Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and turn out onto towel; sprinkle again with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll up.
Cool about 1 hour; unroll and spread on Cream Cheese Filling.

title: creamy beef stroganoff
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch strips.
Brown meat in hot oil in a large skillet; remove meat from skillet, reserving pan drippings.
Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in reserved pan drippings until tender.
Return steak to skillet; add sherry and next 6 ingredients.
Cook over medium-low heat 10 to 12 minutes or until most of liquid evaporates.
Remove from heat; add cream cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in sour cream; return to heat.
Cook just until hot.
(Do not boil.) Serve stroganoff over noodles or rice.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over crackers on baking sheet.
Heat in 275° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Great appetizer or snack.

title: pork chop-rice casserole
directions: Brown chops in Crisco.
Put rice in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Save one tablespoon soup mix and sprinkle remainder over rice.
Add mushrooms and water.
Place browned chops on top of rice mixture and sprinkle chops with remaining soup mixture.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to one hour, depending on thickness of chops.
Remove cover and bake 10 more minutes or until extra liquid is gone.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash; boil until tender.
Drain thoroughly. Then add onions, eggs, salt, pepper, oleo and sugar and mash well. Pour mixture in a baking dish; sprinkle with crumbs.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: crunchy ham casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni and drain.
Blend soup, sour cream and milk.
Combine the ham with the macaroni in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour half the soup mixture over the macaroni and ham. Spread broccoli on top.
Pour on rest of soup mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with onions and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: fantastic fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill and serve with fruit (strawberries, pineapple chunks, grapes, bananas, cantaloupe etc.).

title: e-z barbecue pork chops
directions: Season and fry pork chops until nice and brown in color. Place in baking dish and pour mixture of barbecue sauce and water over chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion buttermilk pie
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar together. Add beaten eggs, flour, cornmeal and vanilla extract; beat until well blended. Add buttermilk and mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and bake 35 minutes or golden brown.

title: chicken log
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then roll in chopped nuts.

title: jackpots
directions: Brown ground beef and minced onion in frying pan.
When brown, add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Heat thoroughly.
Take canned biscuits mashing each flat and putting them into a muffin pan. Fill each with mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well with a hand mixer and pour into a greased casserole dish.

title: taco filling
directions: Brown ground beef in a medium skillet over medium-high heat. Drain excess grease.
Add water and taco seasoning mix and beans. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, add corn stirring occasionally.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and drain cranberries. Chop coarsely.
Add sugar and let stand 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle gelatin over apple juice and soften 5 minutes, then stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Then add gelatin mixture, nuts, apples and celery to berries; mix.
Pour into mold.
Let sit 6 to 8 hours.
A Pyrex bowl is good to use.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add all ingredients except flour. Add flour and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash and onions together in a little water until tender and mash up good. Beat eggs and add with grated cheese. Crumble crackers good and add soup, salt and pepper. Mix all together and sprinkle top with
a few of the crumbled Ritz crackers. Bake at 425° until brown on top.

title: chocolate-dipped peanut butter balls
directions: To large bowl cream together peanut butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add walnuts.
Shape mixture into small balls using level teaspoons of mixture.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Melt chocolate pieces. Coat 1 ball at a time with melted chocolate.
Place on a wax paper-lined tray.
Chill until chocolate is firm.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk. Place bread in greased baking dish. Combine egg, sugar, salt, cinnamon and vanilla. Add milk, pour over bread. Dot with butter. Set in pan of water. Bake in moderate oven 350° 45 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center. Serve with jelly or any desired sauce. May add 1/2 cup raisins, dates, figs, stewed prunes, apricots coconut or nuts before baking.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from bone and chop up.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix well, then add eggs and walnuts. Chill.

title: grandmama suter's rainbow dessert
directions: Whip the cream with sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed macaroons and pecans.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread 1/2 of the whipped cream mixture in the dish.
Dot small amounts of sherbet, alternating flavors for color.
Spread the remaining whipped cream mixture on sherbet.
Freeze until needed.
Cut into squares and serve frozen.
May be topped with whipped cream and fruit garnish, if desired.

title: clam casserole
directions: Strain clams and save the juice.
Saute onion and parsley in margarine until slightly softened.
In large casserole combine strained clams, bread crumbs, onion mixture and Ritz crackers.
In measuring cup put saved clam juice and add milk until you have 2 1/4 cups of liquid.
Pour this mixture into casserole with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: cream puff ring
directions: Put water and butter in pan and bring to a boil.
Add flour and cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Put dough in bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each egg.
Make a circle of Crisco on a cookie sheet or round pizza pan.
Spread the dough on the circle (a cookie shooter can be used, if desired).
Put sliced almonds on the dough.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes (do not open the oven during baking).
Remove tray and cool.

title: sausage stuffed shells
directions: Prick sausage with fork and parboil in small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Chop sausage.
Fry with onion until brown and crumbly.
Stir often. Drain fat.

title: quickie fruit cake
directions: (I add additional cherries and nuts.)

title: pink punch
directions: Mix and freeze all ingredients except sherbet and ginger ale until about ready to serve and take out.
Add sherbet and then ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon and serves about 25.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips in microwave on High until smooth. Add slightly crushed noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Stir together cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
(Cream cheese should be room temperature or microwaved to soften.)
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of a cup cake cup.
Put approximately 1/4 cup of batter in each cup.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and pie filling of your choice. Refrigerate.
Makes about 30.

title: mrs. fields' cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs. Add vanilla and flour to creamed mixture. Add oatmeal, baking powder and soda to mixture. Add the remaining ingredients and mix together.
Make golf ball size balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, just until set.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	and drain.
