Combine all ingredients and place in	a
buttered dish.
Dot with butter and corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed squash mexican
directions: Cook squash in boiling water to cover 7 minutes or until tender but still firm.
Drain and cool slightly.
Remove and discard stems.
Cut each squash in lengthwise; scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Reserve squash pulp.
Saute garlic, onion, green pepper and jalapeno in olive oil until liquid crisp-tender.
Stir in squash pulp and cook, stirring often, until liquid has been absorbed.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper; remove from heat. Add Monterey Jack cheese and sour cream; stir well.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken; take off bone and dice.
Open each roll and starting at big end, place approximately 1 teaspoon of chicken and roll up to small end of roll.
Place in bottom of a greased baking dish.
Pour cream of chicken soup over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until rolls are brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream the oleo, egg and sugar. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Press in bottom of pizza pan.

title: favorite blueberry muffins
directions: In a medium bowl sift first 5 ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal. Gently stir in blueberries.
In a small bowl mix together buttermilk, brown sugar, oil and egg until blended.
Add to dry ingredients, gently stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into 12 paper-lined muffin cups.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake in 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: beer cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Grease and flour pan.

title: lumpi
directions: Roll small amount in one wrapper.
Seal at one end.
With 1 egg, beat in a small amount of water.
Pinch ends also.
Deep fry in a good vegetable oil.
Serve hot with hot sauce.

title: ultimate strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Tear angel food cake into pieces and put into bowl.
Pour mixture over cake.
Add strawberries.

title: baked chicken
directions: Lay chicken in shallow baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add in order, water, vanilla, salad oil and vinegar.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes, unti top springs back when pressed lightly with finger.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan or baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: vegetables for barbecue
directions: Wrap in heavy foil; seal edges.
Place on shelf of grill or oven.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine miracle whip, catsup, and eggs. Mix well. Add all other ingredients except shrimp and paprika. Mix well. Stir in shrimp and chill good. Serve on lettuce and sprinkle with paprika.

title: easy caramel-chocolate sticky buns
directions: Spread frosting in bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Arrange pecan halves over frosting.
Set aside.

title: stir-fry cabbage and shredded meat or poultry
directions: Separate leaves of cabbage and cut one leaf at a time into thirds.
Pile the thirds atop one another and slice lengthwise into fine shreds about 2 inches long.
Drain bamboo shoots; drop into boiling water and simmer 5 minutes to remove canned flavor. Drain, cool and slice into thin strips like the cabbage.
Thinly slice and shred the pork or chicken.
Place into bowl with soy sauce, stirring to coat.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger in garlic and onion.
Drain and place in medium casserole dish.
Drain corn and layer on top of hamburger. Drain green beans and layer on top of corn.
Prepare 6 servings of Potato Buds or other instant mashed potatoes (or make your own) and layer on top of green beans.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is heated through. This dish is easy to double or triple to make a larger casserole.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in a saucepan over low heat. Stir in vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.

title: chicken with plum sauce
directions: Season chicken with onion salt and garlic salt; brown under broiler 5 to 10 minutes.

title: stephanie's taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and cook in dry taco mix.
In separate bowl, mix together the Fritos, cheese, lettuce, tomato and black olives.
Top with meat mixture.
Season with taco sauce and sour cream, if desired.

title: fruit salad #2
directions: Mix well with 1 can of Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in 1 large tub of Cool Whip.
Chill well.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats in a large bowl; add shortening. Cool ten minutes to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to oat mixture.
Add molasses and salt.
Beat in flour gradually.
Knead until smooth looking.
Transfer to Pam sprayed bowl and let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Punch down. Divide in half.
Shape into two loaves and let rise in bread tins before baking at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook together until rice turns yellow, stirring often.
Pour into greased casserole.
Pour 3 cups chicken broth over mixture and cover tightly.
Bake for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, flour, milk and vanilla together.
Put peaches into pan.
Pour mixed ingredients over top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese crab spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and crab meat together thoroughly.
Spread in a flat dish such as a glass pie plate.
Mix ketchup and horseradish together to make cocktail sauce; spread mixture evenly over cream cheese mixture. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In large plastic bag, add potatoes, cut into large chunks, soup mix and oil. Shake until coated evenly. Empty into shallow baking dish. Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Mix flour and butter as for pie dough. Put
in
9 x 12-inch cake pan; spread with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; let cool.

title: speedy orange drink
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender. Cover and blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: ono sashimi
directions: Thinly slice ahi and lay on platter.
Cover with plastic wrap. Use wooden meat hammer to pound thin.
Remove plastic wrap.
Spread minced (or crushed) garlic over ahi.
Grate fresh Parmesan and sprinkle capers.
Chill until ready to serve.
Mix olive oil and seasoned vinegar in a small covered jar.
Shake well.
Just prior to serving, pour vinegar and oil mixture evenly over the dish and enjoy.

title: spinach-rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions; rinse and drain.
Set aside.
Combine salad dressing, soy sauce and sugar in a large bowl.
Stir in rice.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Stir torn spinach and remaining ingredients into rice mixture.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: steak royale
directions: Flour steaks and brown on both sides.
Put in covered casserole.
Cover with onion, tomatoes, water and garlic chips. Bake in slow oven at 250° to 275° for 2 hours.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with flour and pecans.
Press into deep 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes; cool.
Beat cream cheese with confectioners sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Bring sugar, cornstarch and water to a boil in saucepan.
Cool slightly (takes awhile).
Stir in jello and strawberries.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set. May add additional whipped topping, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Bake at 450° (425° for glass pans) for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° (325° for glass pans) and cook 25 to 35 minutes or until knife blade inserted in center comes out clean.

title: orange blush
directions: Combine orange juice, cranberry juice and sugar.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour in club soda and serve over crushed ice.

title: butter roll
directions: Place flour in mixing bowl; add enough milk to thicken like biscuit dough.
Roll out like a thin pie crust.
Cover well with 1 cup sugar and margarine.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Slice and place flat in deep baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup sugar, vanilla and milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss all ingredients lightly.

title: zucchini spinach lasagna
directions: Simmer onion and green pepper in a small amount of water until tender.
Add next 6 ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes. Alternate layers of tomato sauce, noodles, spinach and "cheese" sauce in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: crescent squares
directions: Can substitute pepperoni for thin sliced ham.

title: good and easy pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add flavorings.
Beat in 1 egg at a time, beating well after each. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 300° about 45 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper to make a smooth paste.
Add liquid to flour paste and cook slowly, stirring constantly.
Stir in grated cheese until melted.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Melt German chocolate over hot water.
Add hot coffee to melted chocolate; mix well and cool.
Add brandy.
Whip cream. Fold cooled chocolate mixture into the whipped cream.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell, regular pastry, graham cracker or vanilla wafer shell.

title: louisiana yam casserole
directions: Beat yams, butter, honey and seasonings together in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk, pecans and raisins.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Use banana pepper.
Cut up peppers and winners.
Cook 5 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients while they are cooking, then drain off water and mix together. Heat to a boil and can.

title: scripture cake(kjv)
directions: Look up scriptures to find the ingredients. Mix them all together. Bake at 350°.
Keep checking for doneness.

title: microwave corn on the cob
directions: Corn may be husked before cooking.
Wrap in waxed paper or place in a covered glass dish and cook.
Rotate dish one-quarter turn through cooking time.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil hard for 1 minute the sugar, milk and oleo.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips, oats and coconut.
After it sets awhile, drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator in hot weather.

title: shoestring potato salad
directions: Toss all together.
Just before serving, add 1 (4 ounce) can shoestring potatoes and toss.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into medium sized pieces.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot grease.
Arrange steak in pan or baking dish.
Top with onion and green pepper.
Pour tomatoes (with juice) and enough water to cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
You can add carrots and potatoes to make a complete meal.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian delight
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet. Place half the macaroni in bottom of greased casserole, then put a layer of meat and corn. Make second macaroni, corn and meat. Pour tomato soup over the whole thing and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole(serves 4. preparation time:  30 minutes.)
directions: In a bowl, mix the soup and sour cream.
Put the chicken and broccoli in the bottom of a buttered casserole dish.
Spread the soup and sour cream mixture over the top.
Top with one layer of Cheddar cheese, one layer of Mozzarella cheese and one layer of Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in fat and grated cheese.
Add milk enough to make a soft dough.
Roll dough thin and bake on greased pan in 450° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir together eggs, oil, bananas and sugar.
Stir in dry ingredients that have been sifted together.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Roll rabbit pieces in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown the meat in skillet, using 4 to 5 tablespoons of cooking fat.
Then add onions and lemon juice.
Cook until done.

title: country chicken and sausage
directions: In large open roasting pan, mix potatoes, sausage and oil. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Cut each chicken breast in half. Separate onion into pieces.
Add chicken, onion, bell pepper, water, salt and oregano, tossing until mixed.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Separate beans under running water; drain.
Sprinkle beans over chicken mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, until chicken and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
(Serves 6.)

title: hot buttered rum
directions: In large bowl combine 1 1/2 cups water and the sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Stir in the rum and remaining water.
Pour into 6 heatproof mugs.
Add 1 teaspoon butter to each cup.
Garnish with cinnamon stick.
Serves 6.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put can of milk in pressure cooker.
Cover half of the can with water.
Pressure on 5 pounds of pressure for 30 minutes. Cool by itself.
After cool, open cooker and can; pour in bowl and mix a little.
Pour in graham cracker crust and spread.
Put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and saute onion. Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let set until cool.
Add pineapple with juice and cranberries.
Mix well and pour into mold or 9 x 9-inch dish and congeal.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook
vegetables
according
to package and drain.
Mix cooked vegetables
with
onion,
celery,
mayo, cheese, salt, pepper and paprika.
Pour into well-greased 2 quart casserole. Mix
crushed crackers with melted margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: icing for jam cakegroves, texas
directions: Bring to a boil until a drop in cup of cold water forms a soft ball.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix together in saucepan over medium heat until it boils. Stir constantly. Let cool and pour into a baked 8-inch pie crust. Refrigerate overnight, then top with whipping cream.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg and ginger; set aside.
In another bowl, combine sugar, pumpkin, egg product and oil.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture.
Stir until just moistened.
Add berries and nuts.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: donna's baked beans
directions: Remove the cubes of fat from the pork and beans.
Do not drain the beans.
Spray the baking dish with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix the first 5 ingredients well in the baking dish.
Then, add the cocktail sausages and stir.
You can adjust the amount of ketchup and Worcestershire sauce, so that the beans will be soft and juicy.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir the beans. If they are runny, bake 15 to 30 minutes longer.

title: ginger snaps(in loving memory)
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into balls.
Roll in sugar, don't pat down.
Bake on greased cookie sheets.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Rinse once or twice.
Add all ingredients and stir in salad dressing until mixes well.

title: indian pudding(a 90+ year old recipe)
directions: Mix together the meal and molasses and stir into scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened and remove from heat. Add sugar, egg, butter, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Stir thoroughly.
Put into a buttered casserole and bake 30 minutes in a 300° oven.
Remove from oven and pour cold milk over it and bake for 2 hours more.

title: tuna crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers or party bread. Spread on crackers or party bread.

title: just "cookies"
directions: Spread graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Cook butter and sugar at rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cut "cookies" while warm.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Add flour and sugar to fruit; add beaten eggs.
Put in your favorite crust and dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; then cut to 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: margie's tarts
directions: Mix flour and butter.
Work together.
Add about 1/4 cup of cold water.
Roll in a ball and chill in refrigerator 1 hour at least.
Take out and roll thin.
Use cookie cutters to make round shapes on floured board.
Put filling on one half and fold and seal (half moon shape).
Brush with beaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for approximately 6 to 8 minutes. Remove from pan while hot.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, water and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixture.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded measuring tablespoons 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are set.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overbake.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: white wine cooler with lemon and melon
directions: Cut honeydew melon in half and clean out seeds.
Using a melon-baller, scoop out perfectly shaped melon balls and place in punch bowl.
Add lemon slices.
Pour in lime juice.
Add wine. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Add chilled champagne just before serving.

title: deb's quiche
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and tomato until soft; drain and set aside to cool.
Combine Egg Beaters, sour cream, nutmeg and cayenne with whisk.
Stir in cheese, onion mixture, broccoli, spinach and turkey bacon.
Divide into the deep dish pie crust. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or oleo in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish or pan.
In a bowl mix the sugar, flour, baking powder and milk; pour this over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour one can of pie cherries or any other sweetened fruit.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle sugar over top. Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Sort and rinse cranberries.
Grind.
In medium size bowl, mix Jell-O with enough water to melt.
Mix in sugar, pineapple and cranberries.
Chill until set.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together.
Gradually add flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 2 hours at 325°.
Cool on rack.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Mix both rices, soup, Cheez Whiz and water chestnuts.
Add frozen broccoli last. Arrange in casserole dish.
Layer rice mixture and chopped chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken and vegetables
directions: In a small bowl, mix chicken soup supplement and water; set aside.
In a saucepan, brown chicken, then add all other ingredients including chicken supplement.
Add spices to taste and cook over medium heat until tender.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, 1 cup walnuts, eggs, vanilla and pineapple together and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven fried parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in butter.
Dredge in cracker crumb mixture and place in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Thoroughly brown the meat on all sides in hot fat, turning often.
Add boiling water, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, sliced onions, bay leaves and seasonings.
Cover and simmer.
Don't boil for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking. Remove bay leaves and garlic clove.
Add carrots, onions and cubed potatoes.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.

title: savory bread
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon oil.
Combine Bisquick, ham, remaining 2 tablespoons oil, eggs, milk, mustard, mushrooms and 1/2 cheese.
Stir to mix.
Spread in greased 10-inch casserole 1 to 1 1/2-inches deep.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and sesame seed.
Pour butter on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Separate ham slices and lay on cutting board.
Spread cream cheese on ham slices.
Roll up and slice; secure with a toothpick. Pickles may also be added before rolling and slicing.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour all in baking dish and stir well.
Add meat mixture and stir.
Bake at 275° for about 1 hour.

title: jean's homemade ice cream
directions: Put 1/2 of the milk on stove over medium heat.
Heat until bubbly.
Mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Slowly add to the warm milk.
Beat eggs well. Slowly add to the milk and sugar mixture. Stir while adding eggs. Cook 1 minute.
Add vanilla. Add condensed milk and Pet milk and the rest of the whole milk. Cool before freezing.

title: double chocolate mint chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt 1/2 package of mint chocolate chips in microwave.
Let cool to room temperature.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In separate bowl, beat butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add melted chips and egg; beat well.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes.
Allow to stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheets.
Cool completely. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry hamburger and pour off grease.
Add tomatoes, onion, carrot and tomato sauce; add spices to taste.
Let simmer slowly for several hours.
Cook noodles and drain.
In pan, layer noodles, hamburger mixture, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350 for 30 to 35 minutes, until bubbly.
Can be frozen.

title: german slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in a large plastic bowl with cover.
Top with chopped bell peppers, onions (sliced thin) and sugar (1 cup).
Do not mix or stir.

title: chicken and wine sauce
directions: Dip chicken in egg, roll in bread crumbs, fry until brown on each side and arrange in shallow baking pan.
Saute mushrooms; add pepper, broth and wine.
Thicken with cornstarch (dissolve cornstarch in a little water before adding the mixture.)
Don't add salt.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of Parmesan cheese over chicken; cover with 3/4 of the Mozzarella.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle rest of 2 cheeses on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with wild or white rice.
Serves 4.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours or on high 5 to 6 hours. Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: cleo anderson russell's zucchini pickles
directions: Slice zucchini and onions; cut peppers into stripes.
Layer in large glass or plastic bowl.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 3 hours.
Drain; do not rinse.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar and spices and boil.
Add zucchini; bring to boil up.
Do not cook. Pack into jars.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn and milk over low heat.
Gradually stir in egg; add next 4 ingredients and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches to half fill Pyrex dish (large).
Sweeten with 1 cup white sugar.
Then in bowl, mix together flour, 1/2 cup white sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Crumble on top of peaches, then sprinkle on butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese and noodle kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Combine noodles, eggs, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend milk, cream cheese and cottage cheese in blender or processor until creamy, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add to noodle mixture.
Stir in raisins, butter and cinnamon.
Transfer to prepared dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm or at room temperature with sour cream.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken, dice into small pieces. Cook broccoli, drain. Put chicken in bottom of casserole dish add broccoli. Mix sour cream, soup, butter, add milk. Pour on top of broccoli and chicken sprinkle with cheese. 350° until bubbly.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover; blend on high 15 seconds. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Refrigerate any left over.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put the oysters, the liquor, the butter and milk in a heavy saucepan and simmer until the edges of the oysters just begin to curl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 1.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend together flour, salt and shortening until like fine cornmeal. Mix together egg, water and vinegar. Add to flour mixture.
Makes 4 single crusts or top and bottom crust for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: After the chicken is deboned, cut into chunks in a large flat baking dish (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix milk and 2 cans of soup; pour over chicken.
Put stuffing mix (dry) over the top and melt butter. Dribble over top if not enough; melt a little more.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.

title: taco casserole
directions: Combine beef, taco seasoning mix, canned tomatoes, 1 cup cheese and 1 cup corn chips.
Mix and put in 2-quart casserole. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and top with dollops of sour cream, remaining chips, lettuce, tomatoes, taco sauce and cheese.

title: roasted potato wedges(patate arrosoto)
directions: Wash
and
scrub potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into sixths. Place in pan and sprinkle with fresh garlic, salt, pepper and olive oil.
Bake
at
until
tender,
approximately
40 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle cornflakes over top.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry hamburger; drain off fat.
Add package of taco seasoning.
Mix thoroughly.
Put a dab of taco sauce in bottom of 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Put a layer of corn tortillas, layer of sour cream and cottage cheese, layer of hamburger and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers until ingredients are gone.
Bake at 450° until done, about 1 hour.

title: spiced beets
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill well before serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with approximately 3/4 to 1 cup buttermilk.
Mix well and drop small amount in deep fat.
May add crumbled slices of bacon, ham or green onions to taste.

title: biscuit muffins
directions: Combine sour cream and soft drink in a medium bowl.

Stir in biscuit mix with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon into lightly greased miniature muffin pans. Brush with half of butter. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Brush with remaining butter and serve immediately. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown pork chops quickly in a
hot skillet. Lay chops in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: best salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make enough for several times by tripling the recipe.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and toss all together with 1 cup dressing.
Chill.
You will probably need to add some more dressing before serving.
The spaghetti absorbs a lot of dressing and may be dry.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, oil, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add raisins and pecans; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake 20 minutes.
Chill overnight before slicing.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: chicken and ham roll-up
directions: Pound chicken breasts to flatten and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with slices of ham.
Place 1 tablespoon of cheese in the center of each slice and roll up, then secure with a toothpick and place in baking dish.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Drain peas; place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Arrange eggs over peas.
Spread mushroom soup over eggs.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese, then crackers and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp, corn and potato soup
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in pot.
Saute down.
Add shrimp and cook until they are done.
Add Campbell's soup and cook on low for 30 minutes.
Serves 20-25 people.

title: schnitzel mix for pork chops
directions: First, beat egg and milk together and place in separate bowl. Then mix all other ingredients together in another bowl.
Then dip pork chops in egg mixture first and then in Schnitzel mixture second and then fry.

title: obert's vegetable casserole
directions: Mix cooked vegetables and onions (you can mix in 1/2 cup of mayonnaise with vegetables).
Oil casserole dish.
Place a layer of crackers, then vegetables, then cheese and repeat the layers with final layer of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Heat spaghetti sauce. Drain noodles and place in casserole dish.
Stir in sliced pepperoni and heated sauce and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: canape spread
directions: Fry out meat and drain fat off; add rest of ingredients except bread.
As	cheese	melts,	mix
well with the meat and spices. Spread on
bread
and
place on cookie sheet.
Put in very hot oven for a few minutes until very hot.
Serve immediately.

title: blt pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine half the bacon, cheese, chopped tomatoes, onion and parsley.
Spoon into pie crust.
Beat egg with evaporated milk. Slowly pour over bacon mixture.
Arrange sliced tomato on top of pie.
Bake on preheated baking sheet for 35 minutes (30 minutes for regular crust) or until pie crust has browned or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 15 minutes; top with shredded lettuce and remaining bacon.
Serve.
Makes 8 servings (6 for regular crust).

title: zucchini oats health crunchies
directions: Cream butter and honey. Add beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and shredded zucchini, raisins and walnuts (coconut too if desired).
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: egg salad
directions: Boil eggs for 10 minutes.
Mash with potato masher.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with paprika.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture comes to a boil, boil 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, chocolate and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir vigorously until chocolate is melted.
Stir in nuts and pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix and top with Cool Whip.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Beat together 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 egg and cream cheese.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.

title: fancy brussels sprouts
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring water, parsley, sugar and salt to a boil. Add Brussels sprouts. Cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender; drain. Add water chestnuts and butter; heat through. Yield: 6 servings.

title: old fashion pot roast
directions: Brown the meat in the flour with salt and pepper.
Spread the mustard over it and place in a heavy pan.
Pour the wine and water over it.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
If it gets dry, add a little more wine and water.
About an hour before it is done, add the vegetables.
When the vegetables and roast are done, remove to a platter and make gravy with the juices.
This is a real family meal that is a winner.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: biscuit-sausage roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except sausage.
Roll out in rectangle shape.
Add more flour, if needed.
Spread sausage on and roll up. Cut in half.
Wrap and put in freezer.
When firm, slice.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: a "no-name" berry dessert
directions: Mix berries in large bowl.
Layer bottom of pastry shell with berry mixture.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in medium size saucepan; gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, stirring until completely dissolved. Cool to room temperature.
Pour over berries in pastry shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Spread Cool Whip topping over pie before serving.
Refrigerate any leftovers. Serves 8.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw dough in refrigerator overnight.
Break 1 loaf into pieces.
Roll into balls and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour over dough.
Break remaining loaf and roll into balls.
Fill in holes left by the first loaf.
Let dough rise.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Can be made a day ahead and rewarmed.

title: jean's hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain excess fat. Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until mixture boils, stirring frequently. Cover and simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: basic pizza dough
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast and salt.
Stir very warm water and oil into dry ingredients.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 4 to 6 minutes. Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
On lightly floured surface, form dough into smooth ball.
Divide and shape as directed in recipe.

title: clam chowder
directions: Use very large, microwavable container.
Make roux from 1 stick butter and 1/2 cup flour.
Cook in microwave on High, about 2 minutes.
Stir until it is smooth.
Add roux mixture to clam chowder and place on lower than Medium (microwaves vary, this would be about 4 on a Litton).
Cook in microwave about 1 1/2 hours.

title: avocado and crab dip
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients in large bowl until well combined. (Can be prepared 3 hours ahead, cover and refrigerate.)
Stir crab meat into avocado mixture.
Season with salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: bubble bread pizza
directions: Sprinkle a greased 12-inch pizza pan with corn meal.
Separate biscuits.
Snip biscuits into 4 pieces.
Place in medium bowl. Add spaghetti sauce.
Toss to coat.
Arrange dough in an 8-inch circle in pizza pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 10 appetizer servings.

title: butter pecan turtle bars
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter to fine crumbs.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over crust in pan.
Cook 2/3 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar over medium heat until entire surface boils.
Boil for 1/2 to 1 minute.
Pour evenly over pecans in pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes, until entire surface is bubbly and crust is golden. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let chips melt and swirl them as they melt.
Leave some whole; do not spread them.
Cool and cut into small bars.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips.
Put in a large baking dish.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: monkey cake
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Shake onto biscuits.
Place in layers in tube pan.
If desired, sprinkle each layer with nuts and raisins.
Bring butter and remaining cinnamon and sugar to a boil.
Pour over biscuit mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan immediately. Serve as buns or finger food.
Break apart with two forks.

title: eggplant parmesan(yields 6 servings)
directions: Peel skin off eggplant.
Slice lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle each slice with salt.
Let stand at room temperature 1 to 2 hours.
Wash each slice with water to remove extra salt and squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
Dip each slice first in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry each slice until both sides are golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Cut 1/2-inch strips of Mozzarella cheese and place a strip at the end of a slice of fried eggplant.
Roll eggplant up around strip of cheese and place in a single layer in bottom of a casserole dish. Pour 2 to 3 cups of any tomato sauce over the rolls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour until sauce bubbles.
Enjoy!

title: texas potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine sour cream, soup and butter.
Mix well.
Add salt, pepper, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Mix well. Blend in potatoes.
Place the mixture in a greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle buttered corn flake crumbs on top.
Bake uncovered in oven at 350° about 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white coconut cake
directions: Mix and beat 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Lightly brown beef in small amount of oil. Add all the other ingredients. Cook 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls (size of a quarter).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot.

title: squash fritters
directions: Beat together
egg and milk.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix squash with
liquids.
Add
this
to
dry ingredients and mix. Drop fritters in deep fat with spoon and cook until brown.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Press into 10-inch pie plate. Spray sides with Pam to prevent sticking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Stir all the ingredients together.
Put into small or large greased bread pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Muddle eggs and onions; add to dry ingredients along with buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients, but be careful not to overmix.
Yields 20 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Add sugar to Crisco gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Mix soda thoroughly with flour.
Add to mixture of eggs, sugar and Crisco.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: fondue franks
directions: Cut wieners into bite-size pieces.
Mix and heat mustard and jelly until warm.
Add wieners and cook approximately 10 minutes. Serve as appetizer with toothpicks.

title: italian delight
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add corn, soup, tomatoes, cheese, bell peppers and cooked noodles.
Cook until tender and cheese is melted.
Yields 12 servings.

title: it's my night to cook pasta
directions: Microwave 1 package of popcorn.
Warm the Prego.
Combine the two.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: spring breeze cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with strawberries and cherry pie filling.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat the egg into the mixture.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly golden at edges.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients and sift into medium-large mixing bowl.
Cut butter or margarine into chunks and cut into dry mixture with pastry blender until mixture is size of peas.
Mix in raisins and caraway seed; add milk and egg all at once.
Stir with fork until just blended.
Turn into greased pie plate, mounding in center; with sharp knife, make four slashes in shape of cross.
Bake 30 minutes or until browned on top.
Great with a cup of strong, hot tea on a gray day!

title: cheese-sausage balls
directions: Mix all together; shape into small balls.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cottage cheese rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Heat cottage cheese until lukewarm.
Stir in sugar, salt, baking soda, eggs and yeast mixture.
Gradually add enough flour to make soft dough.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Divide into 24 pieces; shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in approximately two 9-inch square pans.
After rolls have baked, and as soon as you remove them from the oven, you may brush sugar water on top of them if desired.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix one egg, sugar and butter until well creamed.
Add other eggs and beat well.
Add flavorings.
Mix soda with flour.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Frost when cooled, if you like.

title: homemade chalk
directions: Wash and dry egg shells.
Use rock to grind egg shells into powder.
Put powder in a dish.
Measure and combine flour and hot water in another dish.
Add 1 teaspoon of the powder.
Mix and mash until mixture sticks together.
Shape and press into a chalk-stick shape.
Roll the stick tight in a strip of paper towel.
Dry for 3 days, until hard as a rock.
Write with the chalk.
Erase with your shoe.

title: keebler cookie snack
directions: Line two (9 x 13-inch) cake pans with foil and grease.
Cover bottom of pans with whole crackers.
Combine butter, margarine and sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and pour over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove quickly and cool on sheet of foil. (Separate crackers.)

title: dried corn
directions: Mix together (after taking corn from cob).
Dry in flat dishes in sun or in oven at low heat.
Store in tight cans, tin or glass jars.

title: rachel's angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast cake.
Work together.
Cover bowl. Put in refrigerator until needed.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and bake at 400° until brown.

title: light chocolate cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pans with paper bake cups. Melt margarine, remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and dash of salt; add alternately with milk and vanilla to mixture in saucepan.
Beat until well blended. Spoon into bake cups.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack, sift powdered sugar over top.
Yields 18 cupcakes.

title: p-nut butter chocolate chips
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter; add sugars and beat.
Add egg; beat until smooth.
Add flour and soda.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown beef with onion and pepper.
Cook until soft.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rolls and a salad.

title: mimi's zucchini
directions: Wash and slice zucchini not too thinly.
Add very little water and salt.
Parboil on low heat until tender.
Drain well.
Put back into pot.
Add margarine and onions.
Simmer until onions are soft. Put in 12 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex casserole.
Add grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: nutty crunch chicken
directions: Combine pecans, cheese, garlic salt and basil in bowl.
Pour lemon juice into another bowl.
Dip chicken in lemon juice, then cover with pecan coating.

title: seafarer's bake
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Arrange 3 noodles in the bottom of a greased oblong 2-quart baking dish. Press thawed spinach in strainer to remove all moisture.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter.
Add flour, syrup and vanilla flavoring. Pour in buttered and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch frozen pie shell. Top with one regular 9-inch pie shell.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Test.
If not done, bake 15 minutes more.
Remove from oven and cool in pan.

title: chinese beef cubes
directions: Heat fat in large skillet.
Add onions and pepper.
Saute over medium heat until tender.
Remove from fat and reserve. Coat meat with flour.
Brown slowly on all sides in remaining fat.
Add water, spices and reserved onions and peppers.
Cover tightly and simmer until tender.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, sour cream and sugar together, then set aside.
Layer lettuce, green pepper, celery, onion and peas.
Pour salad dressing mixture over it, then top with cheese and bacon.

title: english fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Lightly grease/flour tube pan.
Mix all candied fruit with 1 cup flour; set aside.

title: cottage cheese-whipped cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and serve.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Stir remaining ingredients together.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables; cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add kidney beans.
Cover and simmer until beans are cooked.
Add taco seasoning to dressing and shake well. In large bowl, combine lettuce, cheese and chips.
Mix.
Add in meat and bean mixture and stir again.
Cover with taco/dressing mix and mix well.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni for 12 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Rinse well with cold water.
In heavy saucepan, cook together until thickened sugar, vinegar, eggs, salt, mustard and butter.
Cool then add mayonnaise.
Stir into macaroni.
Add as much onion, celery and sweet pickle cubes as you like.
Use green pepper if you want to. Sprinkle well with paprika before stirring for color.
Sprinkle on top before chilling.
Best if refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: copper country coffeecake
directions: Mix soda and milk.
Add egg, salt, sugar, butter and flour; beat hard.
Add baking powder and beat again.
Pour batter into pan.
Press peeled apple slices into batter.
Sprinkle with combination of granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter. Chopped nuts are optional.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (glass pan at 325° for 45 minutes).
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate leaves
directions: Wipe leaves clean with dry towel.
(Do not use water to clean leaves.)
In double boiler over hot (not boiling) water, melt 2 ounces semi-sweet chocolate with 1/4 teaspoon vegetable shortening.
Using the back of a teaspoon, coat undersides of leaves with chocolate, being careful not to coat edges.
Place on tray in refrigerator or freezer to harden.
When ready to use, loosen edges and gently peel leaves away from chocolate, starting at stem end.

title: mary turnipseed's corn casserole
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in blender.
Mix.
Add corn.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake one hour in a preheated 350° oven.
Serves 12 to 14.
This is absolutely foolproof.

title: one dish meal
directions: Spread in 9 x 13-inch dish in layers, following order given. Bake 2 hours at 275°.
Can place in two 8 x 8-inch pans, freezing one for later use.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done (bubbly around edges).

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over butter.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: apple-cheese pudding
directions: Combine soup, milk, brown sugar and cinnamon in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Add butter, toast, almonds and raisins.
Spoon half of the soup mixture in the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with apples and remaining toast mixture.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 5 minutes more.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hermits
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins; mix well.
Form 3 strips on greased cooking sheet.
Bake 17 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces and cool.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until creamy. Beat 5 to 10 minutes with mixer. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well after each egg. Add alternately sour cream and flour. Add vanilla and almond flavoring. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening until crumbly.
Mix in cup, the water, egg and vinegar.
Combine the two mixtures and mix until all the ingredients are moistened.
Divide into 5 portions. Wrap each in plastic wrap and chill at least 1/2 hour before rolling out.
Dough keeps 3 days in the refrigerator or can be frozen.
Bake pie shells at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 5 pie shells.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Mix flour with sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Combine egg, milk and orange juice.
Add to flour mixture with melted shortening; mix until all flour is dampened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.

title: maw maw's tea cakes
directions: Cream egg, sugar and oleo.
Add milk and dry ingredients; then add vanilla.
Roll and cut out tea cakes.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes or until light brown.

title: easy cucumber pickles
directions: Mix everything together.
Heat to boiling point.
Do not boil. Put into jars and seal.

title: simple salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add together all ingredients except peas.
Add peas to boiling water for few minutes; drain and add to salad.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: chicken crunch casserole
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream; stir into chicken.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish. Crush crackers and mix well with butter.
Spread cracker mixture on top of chicken mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until top is crunchy.

title: deli salad sandwiches
directions: Toast bread.
In small bowl, combine chicken or ham salad, pineapple and pecans.
Spread each of 6 toast slices with about 1/2 cup of mixture.
Top each with another toast slice.
Secure with toothpicks, then cut sandwiches in half. Serve sandwiches immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Marinate chicken overnight.
Bake at 350° for first half hour with chicken in baking dish with half of marinade.
After half hour, drain.
Pour rest of marinade on top.
Bake for another half hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt
margarine
in saucepan;
add
sugar,
buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat by hand until this
mixture looks well blended. Then add coconut; pour mixture in pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°, then bake on 325° until done.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken, chicken stock and soup.
Melt butter; add to flour and milk.
Place on top of chicken mix.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain, then return to skillet.
Add onion and continue cooking slow.
Add celery and bell pepper.
Add cooked rice and cooked diced potatoes.
Add English peas, carrots and chopped cabbage.
Continue cooking slow until cabbage and carrots are just tender.
If too dry, add small amount of water or stock from cooked potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the orange juice.
Beat the egg yolks with the sugar in a double boiler.
When thick, add the gelatin and orange juice.
Add the beaten whites with 1/2 cup sugar.
Fill baked crusts; cover with whipped cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, dressing and vanilla at medium speed.
Add flour and baking soda.
Set aside one cup of batter.
Spread remaining batter into 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Melt caramel in milk in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Top with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with chips and pecans.

title: chicken and beef
directions: Wrap bacon around each piece of chicken.
Line an 8 x 8-inch shallow baking dish with chipped beef.
Place bacon wrapped chicken on top of beef.
Mix soup with sour cream and spread over chicken.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Do not salt.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend well. Store in refrigerator.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add vinegar; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter; pour over beets.
Better if left overnight to improve flavor.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mash mixture several times with potato masher, leaving some pieces of vegetables whole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until soup is heated.
Don't boil. Serves 8.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Combine sugar, flour and oatmeal in bowl.
Add peanut butter, then egg, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Press into a well-greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with Icing.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and biscuit mix together.
Slowly add water until consistency is such that it can be rolled into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes or until browned.

title: cider punch
directions: Boil water, sugar and nutmeg together 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add other ingredients.
Put in punch bowl with cracked ice or ice cubes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken spaghetti-nana corley's
directions: Boil hen. When chicken is cool, debone and set aside, saving broth. Melt butter and brown onions, celery and green peppers. Add green olives, chopped pimentos, mushrooms and cream of chicken soup. Add enough chicken broth to make real soupy and the lemon juice. Then add Velveeta and chicken.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix the enchilada sauce, chilies and soups together.
Layer as follows in casserole dish: chips; half of beef; layer of onions, about 1/2 cup; 1 cup cheese; half of soup mixture.
Repeat layers, top with soup mixture.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: corn and bacon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease standard muffin tins.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain to towels and cool.
Reserve 1/4 cup bacon drippings.
Crumble cooled bacon strips and set aside.

title: hollywood pudding
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together and add eggs and fruit cocktail.
Mix together; pour into greased and floured pan. Sprinkle 1 cup brown sugar over top and then sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans over that.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown
hamburger and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Toast buns and put mix on top.
Serves 6.

title: cheesie potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sausage gumbo
directions: Add gumbo fil 5 minutes after boiling.
Cook until onions are tender.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut up chicken into thin slices.
Saute chicken in oil with garlic until no longer pink.
Add onion and pepper and continue to stir-fry.
Add cumin, oregano and salt.
Just before removing from heat, add sherry.
Warm tortillas one at a time in ungreased frying pan.
Assemble fajitas at the table by placing a large spoonful of the chicken mixture plus any desired garnish in the center of a tortilla; fold up bottom and sides to make fajita.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain
peaches
and oranges, reserving syrup.
Dissolve gelatin
in
2 cups of juice.
Add Knox gelatine that has been dissolved
in
tablespoon of cold water.
Add rest of juice with
enough
water
added to make 2 cups.
This recipe should have
a
total
of 4 cups liquid.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold
in
drained peach and orange slices.
Pour into 2 quart ring
mold or Pyrex dish until firm.
Serve with Orange Cream Dressing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon and gently add the water.
Mix together the sugar, flour and margarine and sprinkle over the apples.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° until apples are soft.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: seven-layer dinner
directions: Place potatoes in the bottom of a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with other vegetables and uncooked meat in order given, sprinkling each layer with a little of the salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in halves.
Layer Twinkies, bananas, vanilla pudding, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Add salsa.
Spread thin layer of chips in large casserole dish.
Add a layer of hamburger mixture, add a layer of precooked, refried beans.
Add a layer of cheeses, add more nachos, then repeat layers until dish is full. Decorate top with more chips.
Bake for 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: quick banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add bananas. Gradually add flour.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into cleaned and oiled cans that you have emptied of their contents.
Pour about 3/4 full and bake in a 350° oven for about 45 to 50 minutes.
You can check these along (some ovens cook faster and the diameter of the cans make a difference).
To remove, just cut the bottom out of the can and push gently.
Enjoy with a dollop of sweet whipped cream.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake one hour at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and pour cake mix over pecans and coconut.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar well.
Dab over top of cake. Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
This looks like an earthquake but very good.

title: chocolate chip drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, combine margarine, sugar and vanilla with wooden spoon.
Beat until creamy. Beat
in eggs. Gradually add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in
chocolate chips
and
nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto
ungreased cookie
sheets.
Bake
in
a
375° oven for 8 minutes
or until lightly browned.
Makes about 8 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Add peanut butter and milk, mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Thaw about 15 minutes prior to serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: In a small bowl stir water, soy sauce, soup mix and ginger until blended.
In a large skillet heat 2 tablespoons corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add peppers and garlic; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Remove.
Heat remaining corn oil in skillet.
Add beef, half at a time; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes. Remove as browned.
Return beef and peppers to skillet.
Stir in soup mixture.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook and stir celery, red pepper and onion in butter over medium-high heat until tender.
Reduce heat; add Velveeta cheese until melted.
Stir in broccoli; heat thoroughly.
Serve with veggies.
Serve hot.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons per 1 cup hot water.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Mix and let simmer and	drink while hot.
Will make the house smell festive for
the
Christmas
season
and very good also.

title: german reuben casserole
directions: Pare and cube potatoes; set aside.
Combine sauerkraut, potatoes, sausage, dressing and parsley.
Spoon into 10 x 6 x 2-inch ovenproof glass baking dish, which has been greased or sprayed with non-stick spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese and green pepper on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: yam puffs
directions: Beat yams until fluffy. Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill, if necessary, until firm enough to roll into balls.
Roll each ball in coconut. Bake in greased baking dish at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: slow-cooking chicken casserole
directions: Cook 2 hours in 300° oven in covered casserole.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt; mix with apples.
Turn into ungreased, square, deep-dish pan; dot with butter.
Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry as directed except roll into 10-inch square.
Fold pastry in half; cut slits near center.
Unfold over fruit in pan; fold edges under just inside edge of pan. Bake 1 hour or until juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.
Serve warm, if desired.

title: celery casserole
directions: Barely cook celery; drain.
Add drained water chestnuts, drained pimentos and the chicken soup.
Put in casserole and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Toward the last, cover casserole with bread crumbs, grated cheese and almonds.

title: baked herbed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until almost done; drain.
Combine butter with seasonings, then with celery and onion, then pour over potatoes and mix well.
Spoon into baking or serving dish; cook for about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: clam casino dip
directions: Saute garlic, onions, parsley, oregano and bread crumbs in olive oil for about 2 minutes, mixing thoroughly.
When onions and garlic start to brown, remove mixture from frypan and mix with clams (and their juice) and cheese.
Pour mixture into baking pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle the top with bread crumbs.
Place in a 375° oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast rounds or crackers.

title: mom's beans
directions: Cook beans on top of stove in water, covering beans 1-inch for 2 hours.
Put in ovensafe dish, add and mix other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 4 hours.

title: christmas fruit pound cake
directions: Combine raisins, fruits and bourbon in a bowl; let soak for several hours.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and nutmeg onto wax paper.
Beat the butter and sugar in a large bowl until smooth.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, alternating with milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in fruits, bourbon and nuts.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, or until top springs back.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Wrap cake in a bourbon soaked cheesecloth, then in foil.
Store in refrigerator 4 to 5 weeks.
Garnish with the chocolate slivers and cherries.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mash bananas in a large bowl.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and egg.
Melt butter in microwave; add it to banana mixture and stir until just blended. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake for 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Pare carrots; cut into small pieces and cook in water until soft (cover with water and boil until dry).
Mash until fine.
Add to mixture of bread, onion, parsley, celery, salt, melted oleo and beaten eggs.
Bake, uncovered, in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Freezes well.
Do not use packaged bread cubes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat all ingredients very well together.
Place in a well-greased pan and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sausage and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to box directions.
Brown sausage, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly add milk, cooking over low heat, stirring until thickened.
Stir in macaroni and cheese mix.
Spoon mixture into greased casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix the above ingredients together very well. If you would like fruit in you ice cream, you should puree about 5 cups of what ever fruit you choose. Add the pureed fruit to the ice cream mixture. Pour into your ice cream churn and begin to churn. This recipe makes approximately 6 quarts of ice cream.

title: best baked beans
directions: I never make my beans the same twice!
Experiment!
I always use the first 3 ingredients listed, but I add any combination of the ingredients that follow.
Whatever I have in my cupboard I use. You definitely want to use some ham and/or bacon, if you are not cooking for any vegetarians, to flavor this wonderfully.
Bake slowly in the oven at 200° for at least 4 hours.
You may need to add more "liquid" ingredients to moisten if you like your beans wet.
These can be done in the slow cooker or crock-pot also, but the flavor is never quite as good that way.

title: chocolate satin glaze
directions: Combine sugar and water in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; immediately add mini chips, stirring until melted.
Continue stirring until glaze is desired consistency.

title: layered spinach supreme
directions: Combine Bisquick, milk, eggs and onion.
Mix well and spread in a 12 x 7-inch greased pan.
Combine remaining ingredients. Spoon mixture over batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in large baking dish.
Mix ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake covered 1 hour at 350°; uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve in hollowed out pumpernickel bread with bread chunks or raw vegetables.

title: twice baked stuffed potato
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 hour after scrubbing and sticking with a fork.
Or wrap in paper towel and stick in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes.
Carefully slit top of potatoes in an oblong oval and scoop out as much as possible.
Place in mixing bowl.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Mash and add remaining ingredients except marshmallows.
Beat well and place in a buttered casserole or glass baking dish.
Dot with additional butter and bake in a 350° oven until very lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently press marshmallows into top.
Return to oven until marshmallows are lightly browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh apple fritters
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil until brown. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Good with Waldorf salad.

title: toffee grahams
directions: Place 48 crackers on a greased cookie sheet.
Bring to a boil the butter and brown sugar.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies. Pour goop over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Takeoff cookie sheets quickly.
When cool, dab with melted chocolate chips.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together all dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk to dry ingredients. Knead dough enough to hold together. Roll dough 1/2 or 1/4-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased sheet; let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken; mix with chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mixed vegetables, if desired.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Slice the boiled eggs over mixture.
Mix butter, Bisquick and milk, then pour over eggs. Cook at 350° until brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Place hamburger pattie in center of double thick 12-inch square pieces of foil.
Add carrots and potatoes on top.
Top with seasons and onion soup.
Add water.
Fold sides up and over several times. Fold ends up to avoid leaking.
Bake at 400° on baking sheet for 1 hour.

title: mud cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs.
Sift flour and cocoa; add and mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 300°.
When done, remove from oven and cover with marshmallows.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes longer.
Let cool before icing.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients with a fork in a bowl.
Mix ingredients only until they hold together.
Shape into a loaf and place immediately in a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 375° or until browned on top.

title: apple cheese quiche
directions: Bake pastry shells at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Layer cheese, sausage, apples and mushrooms in shells.
Combine eggs, flour, salt, milk and butter; beat well.
Pour half of egg and milk mixture into each shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef and drain; add garlic, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain. Finely chop tops and bottoms of green onions and mix with cream cheese and yogurt.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, cream cheese mixture and grated cheese in 2-quart baking dish, ending with cheese on top.
Bake about 20 minutes to heat thoroughly at 350°.
Best mixed the day before.
Serves 8 with seconds; freezes well.

title: little smokie wraps
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put first 2 ingredients at bottom of pan.
Put cake mix on top.
Melt butter or margarine and pour on top, then, if you want, add nuts.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: choco-mint snappers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt mint chocolate chips over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat.
Combine shortening, sugar and egg in bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in melted chocolate and corn syrup.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt and gradually stir into chocolate mixture.
Shape dough into balls, using 1 level tablespoon each.
Roll balls of dough in sugar. Place 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 3 dozen (3-inch) cookies.

title: millionaire fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 3 minutes.
Move from heat; add other ingredients.
Beat until chocolate melts.
Spoon on wax paper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across grain into very thin strips.
(Tip:
To make slicing easier, freeze beef 1 hour.)

In skillet, over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook 1/2 the beef and 1/2 the onion until the beef is no longer pink and onion is tender; set aside. Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to very low.
Stir in sour cream.
Gently heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugars and margarine. Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa. Add flour to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 of chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle nuts and remaining chips on top of cake.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° to 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread("get the coffee cans out")
directions: Grease and flour 3 coffee cans; set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and oil for 3 minutes.
Add pumpkin, soda, water and flour; beat 3 minutes more.
Pour batter into coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Put cheese in crock-pot to melt. Add other ingredients and simmer on low for a long time.

title: pineapple ice
directions: Combine sugar and water; boil slowly for 5 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Add the next three ingredients and mix well.
Pour into refrigerator freezing trays, set at coldest temperature and freeze to a mush.
Have egg whites beaten until stiff.
Turn ice from freezing tray quickly into a chilled bowl, add egg whites and beat hard and fast, then return to refrigerator to finish freezing until firm.

title: gingersnap dessert
directions: Dip each cookie quickly in milk and layer in a glass dish. Next, add a layer of Cool Whip.
Alternate this until you make it the size you want.
Refrigerate.

title: easy cheesy spinach
directions: Defrost spinach; squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients. Put in greased casserole. Bake at 325° for approximately one hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clam juice and pour over vegetables.
Add water to cover.
Simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Melt butter; add flour and blend.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add half and half.
Cook until smooth; add clams and seasonings.
Put together with vegetables. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk and mix well. Sift flour, cinnamon and soda.
Use a very large bowl to mix in. Cut fruit and nuts up and mix.
Pour sugar mixture over fruit and nuts and mix very well.
Use teaspoon and drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix bananas, eggs, sugar and butter slowly.
Add dry ingredients, nuts, vanilla and water.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 1 hour.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Place the popped corn and peanuts in a large bowl or pan.
Cook the molasses, sugar and syrup together until it spins a hair.
Pour immediately over the corn and peanuts, stirring all the time.
Mix well until all corn and nuts are coated.
It will become hard as it cools.
Store in a covered container.

title: cindy rae's buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar; set aside.
Melt the butter. Beat the eggs just a little; add to butter.
Add vanilla and buttermilk, stirring with a spoon or fork.
Pour into uncooked pie shells.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Heat sauce
in a 10-inch skillet.
What you now want to do is dip
a
tortilla
in
the
sauce to make it easy to work with. Place the
tortilla on your Dutch oven lid or plate and add some meat,
onion and cheese.
Roll up and gently place in a Dutch oven or
pan.
When pan is full, pour the rest of the sauce over the enchiladas and sprinkle a little cheese on top. Heat until
sauce bubbles or cheese melts.
Serve warm and top with some sour cream.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Dab on top. Layer grated Cheddar or American cheese, bacon bits and eggs. Cover with Saran Wrap overnight.

title: lemon-pineapple angel cake
directions: Slice cake into thirds crosswise.
Mix instant pudding and pineapple with juice together.
Fold this mixture into Cool Whip. Cover between layers and ice cake with this mixture.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Beat until it's a lemon color.
Stir in zucchini, flour and cinnamon.
Then add the nuts.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy oatmeal squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients together well and mix in oleo.
Line well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan with the crumb mixture (saving 1/2 cup for topping).
Press down with greased spoon or spatula.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together; form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet; brown in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Mix flour and soda.
Add to first mixture and beat well again.
Add apples and pecans.
Mix well. Bake in a tube pan which has been greased and dusted with flour. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream in a large bowl.
Pour mixture into 9 x 11 dish.
Pour salsa over the mixture and then sprinkle with Mexican cheese.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and slice into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Use egg and flour to batter these.
Then fry in olive oil until golden brown.
In bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, put one layer of fried eggplant.
Sprinkle layer of Parmesan over eggplant.
Mix diced tomatoes and pasta sauce in a bowl.
Make a third layer from the sauce mixture.
Repeat layers of eggplant, Parmesan and sauce. Top with generous layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry ring tea bread *
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberry relish and corn syrup; heat just to boiling.
Spoon mixture into greased 6 1/2 cup ring mold. Combine margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spread 1 side of each biscuit with some of the brown sugar mixture.
Place biscuits on edge of ring mold.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan for 3 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: forty niners
directions: Can substitute 1 cup coconut for 1 cup pecans.
Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: waffles
directions: Whip egg whites.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients. Fold in egg whites.
Cook on waffle iron.
Makes 12 to 13 waffles.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil, eggs and sour cream together. In a small bowl, mix 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 2 tablespoons brown sugar; mix by hand. Set aside.

title: chinese cabbage stir-fry
directions: Coarsely chop the cabbage.
Remove root portions from bean sprouts.
Set aside.
Spray wok.
Preheat on high.
Meanwhile for sauce, in dish stir together cold water, soy sauce, cornstarch and garlic. Add cabbage, bean sprouts and onion to hot wok. Stir for 2 to 3 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Push vegetables from center of wok.
Stir sauce, then add to center of wok.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, about 30 seconds.
Add vegetables to coat with sauce. Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings. Contains 36 calories.

title: french silk pie
directions: Using electric mixer cream butter and sugar; add melted chocolate and
vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating for 2 minutes after
each.
Pour into pie shell and chill at least 2 hours.
Top
with
whipped	cream
and
sprinkle with slivered almonds or other nuts just before serving.	Serves 8.

title: creamy chicken stir-fry
