directions: Spray skillet with vegetable cooking spray and heat over medium heat 1 minute.
Add Vegetables and stir-fry until tender-crisp. Set aside.
Remove pan from heat.
Spray with cooking spray.
Add Chicken and stir-fry over medium-high until browned.
Add Soup, Water, Soy Sauce and Vegetables.
Heat through.
Serve over Rice. Serves 4.

title: surbian 1-2-3 nut roll
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add butter, salt and soda; mix well.

title: zucchini omelet
directions: Combine egg, milk, parsley and seasonings.
Add zucchini and cook in a nonstick pan over moderate heat until center is almost set, about 4 minutes. Top with cheese and melt cheese.
Serves 1.

title: "mom's" pecan pie
directions: Mix in a 1 1/2-quart pan the flour, sugar and salt.
Add corn syrup and mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, with a fork. Mix in milk and vanilla and cook on stove top until boiling.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° until firm, about 50 minutes.

title: hot dogs and potato casserole
directions: Saute onions in cooking oil until transparent.
Combine salt, pepper, flour, dry mustard and water.
Add this mixture to the onions.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
In a slightly greased casserole dish, layer potatoes and hot dogs that are sliced lengthwise and placed face down.
Pour sauce over all and bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove from oven and pour vinegar over all.
Recover and bake 5 minutes more.

title: seafood potato chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, combine water and undrained tomatoes.
Crush with potato masher.
Bring to boil.
Add remaining ingredients (still frozen).
Cover.
Place in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally to break up.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: seed bread
directions: Proof the first 3 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients. Knead for about 10 minutes.
Let rise 35 to 45 minutes in greased and covered bowl.
Shape as desired.
Brush lightly with egg whites and sprinkle with poppy seeds.
Bake at 375°.
Makes two 9 x 5-inch loaves or 1 large round.

title: ice box cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and divide into 6 rolls.
Wrap tightly in waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator at least 12 hours.
Slice thin and bake at 375° to 400° for 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Dough will keep in refrigerator 4 to 6 weeks.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven 375°.
Before making cake batter prepare cake topping.
In a 13-inch by 9-inch baking pan place butter.
Place pan in oven until butter melts.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter. Drain pineapple chunks.
Use pineapple in sugar mixture.
Prepare cake batter as recipe directs, and carefully spoon over design in baking pan.
Bake 35-40 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Then loosen cake from side of pan; place platter on top of pan, and invert both lift off pan.

title: apple stuffed acorn squash
directions: Wash squash. Cut in half lengthwise and remove seeds. Place squash, cut side down, in a 13 x 9 baking dish. Add 1/2-inch water and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Turn cut side up and fill squash with 2 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle lightly with salt and cinnamon.

title: smoked turkey soup
directions: Boil carcass and strip meat off bones.
Add all other ingredients and cook until tender.
Recipe can be adjusted to need.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, egg, Crisco and peanut butter; add flour, vanilla and milk.
Mix with mixer and as the dough stiffens, use hands to mix well.
Shape into balls and press down on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Keep checking because these are easy to burn but are delicious.

title: leftover turkey, chicken or pork
directions: Mix all together.
Mixture will be dry.
Top with sliced almonds or croutons.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in Medium microwavable bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Stir.
(Marshmallows will be partially melted.)
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of whipped topping.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add coconut; bake as directed. Remove from pan; punch holes all over cake with a fork.
Pour coconut milk over cake.
After cake completely cools, ice with Cool Whip.
Cover with coconut that is left over.
Place in refrigerator.
Make 24 hours in advance.

title: a modern grandma's micro fudge
directions: In a 1-quart micro-safe glass measure, combine the milk and chips.
Microwave on High (100% power) for 3 minutes.
Stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in salt, vanilla and nuts. Spread evenly in 9-inch square, wax paper lined pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn out fudge on cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Um um good!

title: deviled crab
directions: Rinse crab and drain.
Melt butter in saute pan.
Add flour and mustard.
Cook until it bubbles.
Add milk.
Cook until slightly thick.
Stir in drained crabmeat and sherry.
Season with Tabasco or Worcestershire sauce to taste.

title: fig newton pudding
directions: Crumble Fig Newtons into milk; soak about 30 minutes.
Add sugar and salt to this.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: In double boiler, melt marshmallows with milk.
Break Hershey bars into pieces and add to marshmallows.
Stir until melted. Remove from fire and cool.
Whip the cream and fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate for several hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to directions on box.
Make 1 big cookie on regular pizza pan.
Let cool after baking.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Put ingredients in baking dish.
Add hot, scalding tap water until covered.
Mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Spray with Pam.

title: pasta and clam sauce
directions: Saute shallots and garlic in butter. Add flour.
Add juice from the clams. Add milk and cream of shrimp soup. Stir until smooth.
Add clams and heat through. Serve over hot, cooked pasta. Enjoy!

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and tapioca.
Melt margarine and add orange juice and sugar mixture.
Place thinly sliced apples in pastry recipe of your choice.
Pour mixture over apples.
Cover with pastry strips.
Bake at 400° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: chocolate raspberry bars
directions: Heat oven to 400.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder, and salt in a large bowl.
Cut in the butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg, milk, and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press into bottom of 24 greased and paper-lined muffin cups.

title: angel on horseback
directions: Cut bacon strips in half and stripe sparingly with anchovy paste.
Wrap around oysters and secure with toothpicks.
Broil until done and drain.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: aunt margie's macaroni loaf
directions: Cook macaroni with teaspoon salt.
Drain.
Set aside.
Mix teaspoon pepper with bread crumbs.
Set aside.
Blend egg yolks with milk.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine macaroni with milk and egg mixture.
Add bread crumbs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks and fold into macaroni mixture.
Pour into well buttered mold.
Cover with wax paper and anchor to seal.
Set mold in pan of water and steam in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: granny cookies
directions: Cream shortening and both sugars.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Mix salt, pepper and paprika; put over chicken pieces.
Brown chicken in 4 tablespoons of butter or margarine.
Place in large casserole dish.
Saute mushroom pieces in remaining 2 tablespoons butter or margarine for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over and add chicken broth and sherry.
Cook 5 minutes.
Arrange artichoke hearts between chicken pieces in casserole.
Pour mushroom, sherry sauce over all.
Cover and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve with rice and green salad.

title: grandmother's famous cranberry bread(get mother to help)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda into a large bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly. Add egg, orange peel and orange juice all at once; stir just until mixture is evenly moist.
Fold in raisins and cranberries.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool on a wire rack.
If you choose, you may substitute cranberries for the raisins and have an all cranberry bread.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt 1/4 cup oleo in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Fold in crabmeat.
Spoon mixture into greased baking shells.
Mix bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over crab mixture and garnish, if desired.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Shape and bake in shallow baking dish one hour or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Place first three ingredients in large bowl.
In medium bowl mix the remaining ingredients, then add to large bowl.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 12 hours.

title: carne asada
directions: Mix ingredients except the oil in a bowl and let marinate for at least an hour or overnight if possible.
Coat skillet in oil well and heat on medium high.
Add the marinated beef and any marinade to the oil and cook quickly to desired doneness.
Garnish and serve with salsa, guacamole.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: favorite icebox cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Add egg.
Add flour gradually.
Beat well.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Divide into two or three parts and shape into logs.
Roll in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 1/8-inch or 1/4-inch slices and bake in oven at 350° until browned.
(You can freeze the dough if you prefer.)

title: salmon asparagus pie
directions: Place asparagus in a greased pie plate and sprinkle with cheese, onion, and salmon.
Stir remaining ingredients together and pour on top of salmon.
Bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes. Serve and enjoy!

title: incredible delicious dessert
directions: Make brownies using cake like recipe and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool thoroughly.
Mix mousse mix using whipping cream and regular milk to measure 1 2/3 cup of milk called for in recipe. Crumble half of brownies in bottom of large glass bowl.
Spread half of mousse on top of brownies, then half Cool Whip on mousse. Sprinkle chopped Heath bars on Cool Whip.
Repeat layers and cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight if possible.

title: milky way candy cake
directions: Melt together candy bars and 1/2 stick margarine and set-aside.
Cream 1 1/2 sticks margarine, sugar, and eggs.
Add flour, soda, nuts and buttermilk.
Add candy mixture.
Bake in buttered tube pan at 300° about 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into ball. Chill.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add unbeaten eggs one at a time. Add mashed bananas and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
I use 2 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crab meat.
Add crab meat and mix lightly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Spread mayonnaise over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix mayo and sugar; set aside.
Layer dish with lettuce, peas after they have cooled, cauliflower, eggs, bacon and cheese.
Top with mayo mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: peppermint meringues
directions: Heat oven to 225°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar. Beat until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating 5 to 6 minutes until mixture is very stiff, smooth and glossy.
Gently spoon in a large plastic bag. Squeeze into mounds about 1 1/2 inches in size on cookie sheets. Sprinkle lightly with crushed candy.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
It should look dry, not brown.
Turn off oven; slightly ajar door of oven and let cool.

title: chicken delight
directions: Slice boiled fryer and place on bottom of casserole.
Scald milk and add margarine.
Add bread, broth, soup, onion, salt, pepper and eggs.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put cream cheese in bowl and let warm to room temperature.
Add olives, onions, and one-half of the nuts; knead well with hands; form a ball as you roll it over remaining 1/2 cup of nuts.
If you use foil to roll the cheese ball in the nuts, just wrap the ball in the foil; should be room temperature when served.
May be frozen; will keep in refrigerator about one week.
Serve with crackers (not graham or soda).

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; add milk.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to mixture.
Add vanilla and flavoring.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: stove top squash
directions: Cut yellow squash into thin slices.
Heat olive oil in a non-stick skillet.
Add squash and onions.
Cook over medium heat. Lower heat and cook 15 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pannekoeken
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add milk, flour, sugar and salt.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Tip pan to coat sides and bottom.
Pour in batter and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with syrup or warmed pie filling.
Chop bacon and oven fry it first; pour off excess grease.
Spread bacon evenly before pouring the batter over it.
This gets very high and fluffy, but falls within a minute.
Serves 3.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add sour cream, vanilla and almond extract.
Fold whipping cream into cheese mixture.
Stir in cake pieces.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in bananas and lemon juice.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt, then add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in deep loaf pan, about 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mushroom magic
directions: Place a row of ground meat in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with sliced potatoes and onions.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: green sauce
directions: Mix the soup with equal amount of water; put it in the mixer. Rejuvenate the onion in about 1/4 cup of water.
When the onion is soft, put it in the mixer with the soup.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients, with the exception of the flour, at high speed so it is a creamy consistency.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add enough flour to thicken to the desired thickness.
Taste during the process.
Add salt and pepper as your taste sees fit.

title: green pea salad
directions: Grate onion in mixing bowl.
Drain peas.
Chop the eggs fine. Cut ham in small cubes.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in moderate (350° oven) for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Let stand for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spiced perked punch
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients and place in percolator.
In percolator basket place brown sugar and spices and perk.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut parsley onto waxed paper.
Heat oven to 400°.
Add the sliced onions, potatoes and 2 teaspoons of salt to boiling water. Cook, covered, 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add the milk.
Cook on low heat until smooth and thickened.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole with little butter.
Add layer of onions and potatoes, drained.
Sprinkle chopped parsley over first layer and repeat for second layer, ending with rest of parsley on top.
Cover with sauce and bake for 35 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.
Preparation time is 55 minutes.

title: ranch stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in skillet and drain. Combine meat with the rest of ingredients.
Spray mini muffin pan with Pam cooking spray and press wonton wrapper into cups.
Bake empty for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and fill wonton wrappers with mixture and bake for another 5 to 6 minutes or until bubbly. Enjoy!

title: hot antipasto poor boys
directions: Mix dressing and Parmesan cheese in large bowl.
Add tomatoes, artichoke hearts, pepperoni and olives; toss.
Set oven to broil. Place buns, cut sides up, on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Mix 1 can of soup and 1/2 cup milk. Dip chicken in flour, then soup mixture, then roll in stuffing mix. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: quick vegetable beef soup
directions: In large stock pot, cook the onion and beef in the oil until beef is browned.
Add the tomatoes, potato soup, mixed vegetables and water.
Stir to mix well.
Add the salt, black pepper and Tabasco.
Simmer for about 10 minutes or until all the ingredients are thoroughly heated.

title: spicy beef and asparagus
directions: Partially
freeze
meat,
then thinly slice meat across the grain into bite-size strips.
In a bowl, combine meat with egg white,
cornstarch,
sherry,
salt, pepper and hot sauce, working seasoning
into
meat
with
your
hands.
Set aside. Combine soy,
catsup, vinegar and sugar and set aside.

title: anna's pork chop delite
directions: Spray an 8 x 12 pan with Pam.
Layer sliced white onions on bottom of pan (plenty of onions), then layer California long potatoes, 1/4-inch slices.
Cover with 1 can of stewed tomatoes. Layer center cut pork chops on top.
Add 1 more can of stewed tomatoes.
Put parsley flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: jam filled crumb bars
directions: Blend soft butter and sugar together and add flour, salt and baking soda, then add cereal.
Mix well.
Press half the mix in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread any flavor jam on bottom layer, then top with remaining mix and press down.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage pie
directions: In skillet brown 1 pound sausage and chopped onion.
Drain.
In 2 greased pie plates or 1 large square pan, spread meat.
Sprinkle whole package grated cheese over mixture.
In a bowl, mix Bisquick, eggs and milk and pour over meat/cheese mixture.
Slice bell peppers and place on top.
Cook for 30 minutes at 400°.
Let cool slightly before slicing.

title: potato salad or lettuce dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients until thick and creamy.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° ten minutes before baking.
Grease a 10-inch tube cake or Bundt pan.
Heat the milk, shortening and 1/4 cup water until very warm.
Shortening does not need to melt. Blend 1 1/3 cups flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Blend warm liquids into flour mixture.
Beat with an electric mixer at medium speed, about 2 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally.
Gradually add 2/3 cup of the remaining flour and the eggs and beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Add the remaining flour and mix well.
Batter will be thick, but not stiff.
Cover and let rise in a warm, draft-free place until double in bulk, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: honey ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place ham on rack in an open roasting pan and bake 15 to 18 minutes per pound or until meat thermometer reaches 130°.
Remove ham from oven and increase temperature to 425°.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Place butter in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish or pan in heated oven until melted.
Make batter with flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Spoon peaches over top of batter; add any juice.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift cake mix for finer texture.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Use small amount of Crisco oil to grease 13 x 9-inch pan; tilt pan until oil covers bottom.
Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and 1 cup water in bowl.
Stir with fork until blended about 2 minutes.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Soon as cake is out of oven, punch holes over cake.
Stir Eagle Brand milk and pour over cake. Spread over cake until seeps in. Cool cake completely on wire rack. Then spread Cool Whip over cake.
Add coconut over Cool Whip.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: Proof yeast in warm water and sugar.
Mix milk, butter and sugar well and add to yeast mixture.
Beat eggs and salt together; add to yeast mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, until dough is elastic enough to knead.
Knead 10 minutes and let rise in a buttered bowl until doubled.
Punch down and divide into 4 greased pans.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Yields 4 (9 x 5-inch) loaves.

title: poached trout
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan over medium heat.
Add fish. Sprinkle with lemon juice and sherry.
Add onion, mushrooms, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Garnish with parsley.
Let simmer, covered, until fish turns white (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Do not brown.
This should steam in its own juices.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil the macaroni and the 6 eggs.
Let it cool.
Chop the onion; dice the celery.
Mix all together.
Add the mayo as much as you want.
Same with the salt and pepper.
Boil the shrimp; let it cook, then add it to the rest.
Put it in the refrigerator to get cool, then it's ready to eat.

title: three cheese lasagna rolls
directions: In boiling, salted water, cook noodles as directed.
Drain and cool.
Meanwhile in medium bowl, thoroughly mix Ricotta and next 5 ingredients.
Cut lasagna noodles in half crosswise.
On each half, evenly spread 1/4 cup cheese mixture.
Roll up each noodle jelly roll fashion.
Into 13 x 9-inch baking pan, spoon 1/2 the spaghetti sauce.
Arrange rolls in pan; top with remaining sauce. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: saucepan chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in cocoa.
Add milk, peanut butter and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or cookie pan.
Cool.

title: four can casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soups and milk, mixing well.
Reserve a small amount of noodles for topping.
Stir remaining noodles into chicken mixture.
Spoon into greased 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Top with reserved noodles.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, turning dish after 5 minutes.
Let stand for several minutes.

title: creamed canned tomatoes
directions: Simmer tomatoes, minced onion, salt, paprika, brown sugar and celery gently for about 10 minutes.
Combine flour and milk or cream until smooth and bring to a boil.

title: corn dog batter
directions: Put enough milk with all the ingredients to make a thick batter to dip for corn dog.
Can also be used for squash, onion rings or egg plant.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in 10x sugar (criss cross).
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: salsa cruda(no fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir to mix well. Cover and refrigerate.
This sauce may be used as a dip for tortilla chips.
(For a large group, simply double or triple quantities listed.)
It is also used as a topping for Mexican dishes, such as beef tostadas.
Serves 12 (1 tablespoon per serving).

title: lemon sorbet
directions: Combine boiling water and sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add lemon rind and juice.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch square pan; freeze until firm.
To serve, let mixture stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Yields 4 cups.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots, reserving juice.
Add enough water to apricot juice to make 4 cups.
Heat liquid.
Add jello and dissolve. Sieve apricots and add to jello. Let set.
Cream the softened cream cheese and add drained pineapple. Spread over firm jello. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: Spray a 9 x 5-inch pan with Pam.
Shape mixture into a loaf and bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Bake uncovered.

title: baked scallops
directions: Wash scallops.
Melt butter.
Squeeze garlic cloves and add to melted butter.
Pour this mixture into lasagna type pan.
Put flour into a plastic bag and add scallops.
Pick scallops out one at a time and lay in pan.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Broil for 7 minutes or until cooked and brown.

title: sweet and spicy nuts
directions: Combine nuts in bowl and set aside.
Combine egg white and water in medium size mixing bowl; beat at high speed with electric mixer until frothy.
Stir in sugar, salt and spices.
Pour egg white mixture over nuts; toss until nuts are coated.
Spread nut mixture onto a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 275° for 55 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Store in airtight containers.
Yields 6 cups.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions, then drain.
Prepare taco seasoned meat as directed.
Crush half the bag of Doritos and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Spoon half of taco meat mixture over chips, then sprinkle with half the cheese.
Repeat with layers of crushed chips, meat and end with cheese.
Cover and bake approximately 20 to 30 minutes in 300° oven.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight and bake in uncovered casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sheath cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a bowl and set aside.
Put on stove to boil: oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
After this comes to a boil, add it to the flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Then add: buttermilk, soda, beaten eggs, vanilla and cinnamon; mix well. Bake at 400° until done, 30 minutes.

title: martha washington
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well; roll into balls.
Chill well.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over hot water.
Stick toothpick into candy balls and dip into chocolate.
Lay on wax paper.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Melt butter; add pepper and onion.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add flour and milk, then crabmeat and salt.
Cook for 10 minutes. Pour in shallow buttered baking dish or use crab shells.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese is brown.

title: cinnabon rolls
directions: In a bowl, combine water, yeast and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, prepare pudding mix according to pkg. directions, using room temperature milk.
Add 1/2 c. melted butter, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Combine with yeast mixture, mixing well.
Gradually add flour, kneading as you would any yeast dough.
Place in a greased bowl, cover, and let rise until about doubled.
Punch down and let rise again.

title: sugar substitute
directions: When replacing sugar with honey in a recipe, reduce the amount of liquid by 2 tablespoons for every cup of honey used and reduce oven temperature by 25° to 30°.

title: microwave baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Slice through top of each potato.
Pour 1 or 2 tablespoons of Italian dressing into the potato.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and bake in microwave.

title: bacon and tomato quiche
directions: Mix flour and salt; add cut up margarine and cream cheese. Mix with hands until a ball is formed.
Set aside for 30 minutes. While waiting, cook bacon; chop the tomato and cut the cheese into long strips.
Mix sour cream, eggs, salt and margarine in medium bowl; set aside.
Roll out dough and place in a deep dish pie plate or quiche pan.
Layer 1/2 of bacon and tomato, then 1/2 of cheese and then repeat.
Pour sour cream mixture over that. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: banana cake
directions: *Overripe bananas seem to make the best cake.

title: cream cheese-pineapple biscuits
directions: Press fingers into center of each biscuit, making deep indentation about 1 3/4-inches wide.
Fill indentation with cream cheese.
Arrange crushed pineapple around outside edge of cream cheese.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired.
Bake as directed on biscuit package.

title: squash and apple casserole
directions: Cut up squash in large chunks and boil until tender. Remove skin and cut into small pieces. Pare and cut up apples and boil until tender. Butter baking dish. Add 1 layer of squash, then layer of apples. Dot with butter. Sprinkle on salt and brown sugar. Make 3 layers. Top entire dish with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (1 stick).
Layer other ingredients in dish in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs good, add brown sugar, beat until thick.
Add pecans and coconut (tossed with 2 tablespoons flour).
Add vanilla and salt.
Spread over baked crust.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut in squares.

title: homemade sangria
directions: Mix well.
Garnish pitcher with slices of orange, lemons and cherries.
Serve on the rocks.

title: grandma's potatoes
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.
Take salt pork and onion and cut in small pieces.
Fry salt pork; when grease starts coming out, put in onion and fry until brown.
Drain potatoes; place salt pork and onion mixture into mashed potatoes and mix.

title: herb filled croustades
directions: Cut 3-inch rounds from each slice of bread with a 3-inch plain or fluted cookie cutter; press carefully into well-buttered tiny muffin tins (about 2 inches wide).
Bake in preheated 400° oven for about 10 minutes until rims are lightly browned.
Fill with the following:

title: butter balls
directions: Cream together 2 sticks oleo, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Gradually add 2 1/4 cups plain sifted flour. Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix green beans, corn, soup, sour cream, Velveeta cheese and onion.
Place in greased casserole pan. Top with crushed Town House crackers drizzled with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potatoes romanoff(servings: 6.  preparation time: 1 hour and 30 minutes.)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mash with butter, sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate lover's trifle
directions: In a large bowl (snifter or trifle bowl), place 1 layer of cake.
Spread 1/2 of pudding over cake.
Sprinkle over 1/2 brickle bits and Hershey bar.
Cover with 1/2 container Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: cake-type brownies
directions: Melt shortening with chocolate in microwave or over low heat; stir.
Cool.
Stir sugar into beaten eggs, then chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: suet pudding
directions: Grind suet and raisins together.
Sift flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Mix molasses, sugar and milk together.
Work some flour mixture into the suet and raisins.
Then combine all ingredients.
Steam in greased cans for 3 hours. (Pudding will double while cooking.)

title: sweet and sour pork or chicken
directions: Cook green peppers in boiling water until almost tender, about 8 minutes.
Heat with oil, salt and garlic in a frying pan.
Beat egg, flour, salt and pepper together to make batter.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in 1 stick margarine.
Add corn, beans, soups, sour cream and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Melt 4 teaspoons margarine in medium skillet.
Add crackers and stir until slightly brown.
Sprinkle on casserole. Bake at 350° until brown (30 to 40 minutes).

title: mom's carrot bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add currants, coconut and nuts. Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Fill 4 greased 1-pound tin cans about 1/2 full.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour, or until knife comes out clean.
Cool slightly; remove from cans.
When cold, wrap in Saran Wrap, then foil and refrigerate.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: seafood newberg(makes 20 servings.)
directions: Melt margarine and flour together to make a paste. Cook 3 minutes; slowly add milk, stirring to eliminate lumps. Cook until thickened. Add remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated. Serve hot with rice or patty shells.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill well.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Make a 3 layer yellow butter cake.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese with sugars, mixing well.
Add Cool Whip.
Place on first layer of cool cake, and then place about 3 or 4 tablespoons of canned blueberry pie filling.
Repeat layers.
Chill.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers and 1 stick of oleomargarine together.
Put into oblong Pyrex pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks of oleomargarine together and mix well.
Pour over mixture.
Cut up 5 bananas and put on top of previous mixture. Spread 1 large Cool Whip over mixture.
You can add nuts or fruit, if desired.

title: uncooked frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, salt, syrup and vanilla in a bowl.
Beat until frosting is of fluffy spreading consistency.
Will frost tops and sides of two 8-inch layers.

title: family favorite congealed salad
directions: Pour peaches in a colander and drain well.
In a large bowl, chop the peaches very well.
Add cottage cheese and stir, then Cool Whip.
Slowly fold in the dry jello.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: tornado cake
directions: Place cake pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour strawberries and jello over cake.
Set in refrigerator to jell, then top with Cool Whip.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in medium-heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with additional pecans, if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: mexican hot dogs
directions: Cook tortillas in water according to package.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Place a hot dog in each tortilla; top with 2 tablespoons chili mix.
Roll tortillas around hot dogs.
Arrange seam side down in baking dish.
Combine remaining chili mixture and tomato sauce; pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese when pulling out of oven.

title: oriental salad
directions: Pour mixture over vegetables.
Cover and chill 24 hours. Drain before serving.

title: aunt lois' caramel icing for 2 layers
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter or margarine and Pet milk and bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Cover until slightly cooled.
Add baking powder and vanilla flavoring.
Whip until mixture starts getting thick.
If too stiff, add small amount of Pet milk.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: About 25 minutes before serving:
Wash lettuce and drain well; cut into 2-inch pieces.
Remove chicken from bones; discard skin. With fingers, tear meat into shreds.
Cut each cherry tomato and olive in half.
In a large bowl, combine lettuce, chicken, cherry tomatoes, olives, Parmesan cheese and black pepper.

title: peach jelly
directions: Mash peaches.
Add sugar and cook 20 minutes.
Add jello and cook 1 minute more.
Pour into jars; when set, place in freezer. Makes about 1 quart.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute the celery, onion, bell pepper and shrimp in the oil. Add the rice, soup, crabmeat, Tabasco sauce, cayenne pepper and mushrooms.
In a separate pan, melt the cream cheese and margarine.
Mix everything together.
Put in a casserole dish. Grate sharp cheese over top to cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Fry and drain hamburger and onions; stir in sauce mix, water, basil, salt and pepper, tomatoes (with liquid) break up the tomatoes.
Heat until boiling; reduce heat and cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and mixed vegetables (with liquid), cover and cook until macaroni is tender.
Stir in parsley.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Put all ingredients into blender jar.
Blend.
Pour into saucepan.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour into soup cups.
Sprinkle on chopped peanuts.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup servings).

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in heavy skillet.
Melt chili and tomato soup with 1 can of water.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste with chili powder, garlic, salt and pepper. Simmer 3 hours, stirring often to prevent sticking.
This chili freezes very well.

title: apple cider pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beat well after each.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add milk, oleo and sugar. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
The icing may seem to be thin. Adding the vanilla, pecans and coconut will help to thicken the icing. Spread on 2 or 3 layer cake.

title: tim's favorite marinated kibum
directions: Cook noodles according to directions and drain.
Shred kibum with chopper or shredder.
Drain peas and mix all three ingredients together.
Mix onion, green pepper and celery in mixture.
Pour free Italian dressing over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well all the ingredients.
Shape into a loaf in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Pour barbecue sauce on top of meat loaf.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes or until cooled.
Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add the oatmeal mixture and cinnamon.
Sift together soda and flour and add to mixture.
Add raisins.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven; cool and add topping.

title: green tomato sauce-guatemala(salsa de tomate verde)
directions: Put tomatoes, garlic, and hot peppers and cook together for a few minutes until the tomatoes have disintegrated, stirring a few times.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook for a few more minutes or until mixture is well blended.
Bottle and refrigerate.

title: onion rice
directions: Boil water.
Add margarine, soup and uncooked rice.
Blend well and bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This may be baked, covered, or uncovered.

title: lemon gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in jello mixture.
Beat until smooth. Add vanilla oranges, pineapple, soda and pecans.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly.
Fold Cool Whip in.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours until firm.
Cut into squares and garnish with remaining topping.
Yields 16 to 20 squares.

title: florida squash delight
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Add margarine and mash.
Combine remaining ingredients, except breadcrumbs and pecan halves.
Add to squash.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole. Top with breadcrumbs; dot with margarine.
Garnish with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin crumble
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs, pumpkin pie spice and salt into bowl; mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with cake mix.
Drizzle butter over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: goofy butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine, egg and nuts and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours (can be fixed the night before).
Just before serving, sprinkle bacon bits on top.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 2 minutes. Pour into pie shell and bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake until filling is firm.

title: kentucky crab dip
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft and mixable.
Cut onion into small fine pieces. Mix into cream cheese.
Finely chop crab meat, mix into cheese mixture and add remaining ingredients into cheese mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: cavatini
directions: Toss pasta after cooking.
Brown beef and onion; add pepperoni just long enough to heat well.
Drain grease from meat; add spaghetti sauce to meat.
Pour 1/2 cooked pasta in a lightly greased casserole; spoon on 1/2 meat sauce and spoon on cottage cheese over meat.
Add rest of pasta; put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: 3 in 1 made at home cookie mix
directions: Mix well until crumbly.
This can be kept in refrigerator in tightly closed container.

title: light and fluffy cheesecake
directions: To make crust, mix graham cracker crumbs, oleo and powdered sugar. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 450° for 2 to 3 minutes; do not overbake. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and set aside.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Cook onions in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
In mixing bowl, combine eggs and cream.
Stir in onions, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper, nutmeg and ginger.
Add meat mix well by hand or on medium speed of electric mixer.
Shape into 3/4 to 1-inch balls.

title: ham and potato chowder
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and celery in butter until soft. Add ham and potatoes.
Fry for 10 minutes or until done.
Remove from heat and add flour and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add milk. Return to heat and warm slowly.
Serve piping hot garnished with parsley flakes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit fizzie
directions: Mix concentrate with club soda.
Serve cold.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool; mix and add to crust the Dream Whip, milk, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix and add to pan pudding and 3 cups milk; cool.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts; cool. Serve.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Combine skim milk, tapioca, sweetener and salt; let stand 5 minutes.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat (mixture will be thin).
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Gradually fold in hot mixture.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: homemade ice cream(4 quarts)
directions: Beat eggs separately.
Whip whipping cream.
Stir in sugar and eggs.
Add all ingredients together, then pour in container. Fill to 1 inch of top with milk.
Freeze.

title: tempura (shrimp batter)
directions: Beat eggs and water until frothy.
Beat in the flour and salt. Set batter in a bowl of ice to keep cold while frying the shrimp. Always dry the shrimp before putting in the batter.
Fry in oil.

title: super bowl dip
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender in large skillet over medium flame; drain.
Add cubed cheese and chili.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, press out 1 can of crescent rolls, pinching seams together to make a flat crust.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on crust.
Put other can of crescent rolls on top of cream cheese.
Dot butter over top of crust.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
After taking out of oven, drizzle glaze over top.

title: vegetables hot and cheesy
directions: Mix soup together.
Put one bag of frozen vegetables in dish. Spread half the soup mixture and half the cheese.
Add the other bag of frozen vegetables.
Add the rest of soup mixture and the rest of the cheese.
Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meatballs and rice
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, eggs, onions, parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Make 15 small meatballs.
Combine juice and tomatoes, 1/2 teaspoon salt and water in large skillet.
Bring mixture to a boil. Add meatballs.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove meatballs from liquid and thicken liquid for gravy.
Mix 1 tablespoon flour to 3/4 cup water and pour into tomato mixture. Add meatballs and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: carolyn's best cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water for about 3 minutes.
Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat with beater until bubbles appear.
Slowly add 5 1/4 cups flour.
Stir with spoon, making a soft dough.
Knead on board for about 5 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with margarine and add sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up as jelly roll and stretch; cut.
Place each cinnamon roll on greased pan.
Allow to rise until double.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing while hot.

title: frank reuben
directions: Lightly butter toast.
Arrange 3 frankfurter halves on each toast slice.
Divide sauerkraut among sandwiches.
Spoon 1 tablespoon dressing on each.
Top with 1 slice Swiss cheese.
Wrap each sandwich in paper towels.
Place 2 sandwiches on microproof plate.
Cook on High 2 1/2 minutes, or until cheese is melted and sandwich is hot.
Repeat with remaining sandwiches.
Top with additional dressing, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (a little less time if shredded potatoes are used).
Serves approximately 6 to 8.

title: cream cheese filled cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy; beat in egg and dash of salt. Stir in chocolate chips; set aside.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, melted margarine and syrup.
Add nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near middle comes out clean.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well with electric mixer on low, until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (large 9-inch).
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 350° until set in middle, 45 minutes or more.

title: tennessee pride chili
directions: Saute sausage and ground beef with onion, green pepper and garlic in a large, heavy saucepan until browned, stirring to crumble sausage.
Drain excess grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Break tomatoes with back of wooden spoon.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Additional water may be added if needed. Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon jello
directions: Top with Cool Whip before serving.
Can change to sugar-free, by substituting sugar-free jello, Diet 7-Up and natural pineapple.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Dissolve cherry, lemon and orange gelatin separately, using 1 cup of the boiling water for each flavor.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to each flavor.
Pour each flavor into separate pans.
Chill.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Dissolve orange-pineapple flavor gelatin and sugar in remaining cup of boiling water.
Add pineapple juice. Blend Cool Whip into orange-pineapple gelatin. Fold in gelatin cubes.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan or 8-cup mold.
Chill overnight or until firm.

title: true grits
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour onto baking dish and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa and brown in butter in frypan.
Place in deep baking pan.
Saute sliced peppers, onions and carrots and add to kielbasa.
Drain pineapple juice into frypan; add pineapple to Worcestershire into pineapple juice and heat until it forms a clear liquid.
Pour liquid over meat and vegetable mixture and stir together.
Bake for at least an hour at 350°.

title: kurimanju
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Cook beans slowly until the skin comes off.

Mash beans until soft (like mashed potatoes) in strainer, placing pan under strainer for the bean pulp and water (run faucet water through strainer to help wash pulp down). Strain beans until only skins are left in strainer.
Throw away the skins.

title: lemony pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling, salted water for 4 minutes.
Drain well.
Return to pot and toss with remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cindy's tropical spinach salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Toss with dressing and almonds just before serving.

title: sunday supper salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling liquid (reserved pineapple juice and enough water to make 1 cup).
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and walnuts; mix well.
Pour half the mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm, leaving other 1/2 at room temperature.
Spread sour cream over congealed layer.
Top with remaining mixture.
When set, spread Cool Whip over top.
Makes 24 servings.

title: oatmeal drops
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, salt and soda and add to mixture, beating well.
Add raisins, nuts and oatmeal and mix well.

title: seafood tart
directions: On a large round tray or plate, layer the following:

title: alex's chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl and set aside.
Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat Well.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chunks.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 8 - 10 minutes till golden brown.

title: chicken creole
directions: In a large skillet, melt oil and margarine.
Add vegetables and stir fry over medium-high heat until somewhat softened, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste and blend with vegetables.
Turn heat to high, adding water a half cup at a time and blending.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken and bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer and cover skillet.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add chicken.
Simmer 10 more minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over hot rice.

title: caramel breakfast ring
directions: Place custard cup in center of a glass 1 1/4-quart casserole dish to form ring.
Place brown sugar, butter and water in a glass measuring cup, heat for one minute in microwave.
Stir ingredients and add nuts.
Separate biscuits and cut into quarters with kitchen shears.
Place in glass dish.
Spoon caramel mixture over biscuits.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes in microwave, rotating halfway through cooking time.
Rest for 2 to 3 minutes, covered with glass lid.
Invert on a plate and serve while warm, pulling apart.
May be baked in oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until light brown.

title: banana punch for a bunch
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar dissolves and then cool. Blend bananas, sugar, water and pineapple juice in blender. Mix frozen juices with water called for on can. Mix all together.

title: delicious sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Mix all ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake 50 minutes more or until filling is firm.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook in skillet over medium heat the ground beef; drain grease into can provided.
Spread on cookie sheet the tortilla chips.
Sprinkle cooked ground beef over chips. Pour tomato sauce evenly over all.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa with sugar and salt.
Add milk; bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cook until small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Heat until creamy.
Add nuts and pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 the amount of cheese and 1/2 the can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered.
Add remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil all but soda 5 minutes and add soda.
Pour and mix over popcorn and bake 1 hour at 200°.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; stir gently.
Add dry mix to egg; mix until smooth. Stir in butter or oleo.
Pour into shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg lightly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until set.
Cool on wire rack.

title: make ahead spaghetti casserole
directions: Toss noodles with one egg; mix sauce, beef, onions and mushrooms.
Mix noodles and sauce mixture.
Layer noodles and sauce with cheese, saving some for top, in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can freeze or bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Cook and stir meat and onions in large skillet over medium heat until meat is brown and onions are tender; pour off excess oil.
Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir liquid and mushrooms into meat and onions.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: molly's strawberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Place sifted ingredients in a large bowl and make a well in center.
Place strawberries (with juice), eggs, oil and pecans in well; stir until ingredients are moistened.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test after 1 hour.
Cool in pan 30 minutes before turning onto rack.
Bread freezes well.
Makes 2 large loaves or 3 small loaves.

title: stir-fry zucchini
directions: Heat these ingredients in skillet.
When very hot, add 1/4 cup water.
Cover for a few minutes.
Then add liquids and stir until sauce is bubbly and clear.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: In casserole dish melt the butter.
Pour the butter over crushed crackers and stir.
Put drained cooked vegetables in greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and put over vegetables.
Top with crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with chocolate or vanilla frosting.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: working mom's shrimp
directions: In small bowl, stir first three ingredients until smooth.
Set aside.
Generously spray large skillet.
Heat over medium heat. Add shrimp, vegetables and garlic.
Stirring constantly, cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir sauce mixture; add to skillet, stirring constantly, and bring to boil.
Boil one minute.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baking powder
directions: Mix all together and store in an airtight container.
(Same as Royal baking powder.)
Use in recipes that call for baking powder in equal proportions as called for.

title: brisket
directions: Remove fat from brisket.
Place in pan.
Combine chili sauce, brown sugar, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over meat.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery slowly for 20 minutes.
Add cooked rice and rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor and blend thoroughly.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: mock egg salad sandwiches
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, pour Egg Beaters in and cover tightly, cooking over a very low heat for 10 minutes or until just set.
Remove from skillet and cool completely.
Chop into fine pieces.
In a bowl combine the hard-cooked Egg Beaters, mustard, mayonnaise, celery, red pepper and scallions.
Divide and spread on 6 bread slices.
Top with lettuce and remaining bread.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat and remove grease.
Add all ingredients, bring to a boil and let simmer until potatoes and carrots are soft.
(The meat can be rolled in flour before it is browned.)

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Put sugar and cinnamon on top before baking. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grilled shish kabob
directions: You will also need 8 (10-inch) metal skewers.

title: spanish style chicken with yellow rice
directions: In heavy Dutch oven, saute chicken in oil for 10 minutes, or until partially cooked or golden.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons oil; push chicken to sides of pan.
Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is tender.
Stir in paprika, turmeric, salt and pepper, then rice; mix well.
Add water and bay leaf; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add peas; cook for 10 minutes, or until chicken, rice and peas are tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and pineapple (with juice), flour, baking soda, salt and lemon extract.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350 for 12-15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let stand a few seconds before removing to cooling racks.

title: spinach au gratin
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly; chop coarsely. Cook with water clinging to leaves in a covered saucepan until just tender. Cook bacon until crisp, reserving 1/4 c. drippings. Return 2 Tbsp. bacon drippings to skillet; blend in flour, stirring until smooth. Add milk gradually; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add cheese, stirring until melted. Combine cooked spinach and cheese sauce; spoon into a greased 1 qt. casserole. Crumble bacon over top. Combine breadcrumbs with remaining 2 Tbsp. reserved bacon drippings; sprinkle over bacon. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until breadcrumbs are browned.

title: squeeky slaw
directions: Mix the ingredients, except boiling water.
Pour the boiling water over; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain the salted water off the cabbage, but do not rinse.
While this is draining, mix the dressing.

title: slushy punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups cold water. Add juice and sugar and stir.
Freeze until slushy.
Put in punch bowl:
1/2 punch and 1/2 ginger ale or Sprite.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until sugar dissolves, then cook over low heat without stirring to hard ball stage (265°).
Test by dropping a few drops in a cup of cold water.
Meanwhile beat egg whites and salt until stiff but still moist.
Slowly pour hot syrup over egg whites.
Continue beating until it begins to thicken.
Add vanilla and nuts; drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix well and chill.
Pretty, quick and easy to make.

title: butter drop biscuits
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in sour cream, then stir in flour.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375° in a small muffin pan.
Makes about 24 biscuits.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix lightly through strawberries (berries should be halved).

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar, egg, flour, vanilla, nuts and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: After cabbage is sliced and diced, put in large bowl.
Crush noodles.
Add seeds in another bowl.
Mix seasonings, oil, vinegar and sugar.
Mix and toss with cabbage.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy kisses, in large bowl. Mix until dough firms.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll into sugar.

title: parmesan biscuits
directions: Cut canned biscuits into halves.
Roll each in melted butter or margarine.
Dip into mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake as directed on can of biscuits.
Serve hot.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together. Make paste of coloring and cocoa; add salt, buttermilk, vanilla and vinegar. Blend. Add sifted cake flour and soda; blend. Do not beat. Bake at 350° in two 9-inch or three 8-inch pans for 30 minutes. Cool and split layers. Frost between and top and sides.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Place pan in oven to warm.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in a large bowl.
Pour half of batter into warm prepared pan.
Sprinkle half of cheese over batter. Spread remaining batter over mixture and top with rest of cheese. Bake for 35 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.
Each serving contains 199 calories (51% from fat).

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour, then add eggs.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Grease two 9-inch pans.
Pour in pan and bake 35 minutes at 350°, or until brown on top.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and pat in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: chili con quotis
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add peppers and Worcestershire sauce.
Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Add to cheese the chopped tomatoes along with onion mixture.
Add cornstarch, stirring until thick.
Serve hot in chafing dish. Dip with corn chips.

title: lemon cake filling
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil and then stir in sugar and flour mixed together.
Take from fire and add eggs and butter. Set back on fire until egg is set.

title: cheddar vegetable squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Chop the onion.
In a large frying pan, heat the oil over medium heat. Add onion. Cover and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables, marjoram, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Cook until tender, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.

title: curried vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, cook potatoes and onion in hot oil until the edges start to brown.
Add water, curry powder, salt, garlic, ginger and red pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cauliflower; cook about 5 minutes more or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen peas; heat through, adding a little more water if necessary.
Makes 4 to 6 side dish servings.

title: reese's roll
directions: Melt
margarine
and chocolate chips, then add to sugar and vanilla.
Press
mixture
onto wax paper on cookie sheet. Frost with peanut butter and roll.
Cut into slices.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly.
Heat in saucepan over low heat. Slice wieners in bite size pieces or use Little Smokies.
Place in sauce.
Simmer and serve.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Briefly steam and cool the asparagus.
Mix together olive oil, garlic, dill, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Cut stems from the mushrooms and slice.
Peel, seed and slice the cucumbers.
Peel and quarter the tomatoes.
Place all the vegetables in the bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Drain the oil and arrange on chilled platter.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream cheese, butter and margarine with sugar. Beat in 1 egg at a time. Add flour. Beat until smooth. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Mix well. Grease and flour large tube pan or 2 loaf pans. Heat oven to 325°. Bake large pan 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: donna's yummy jello
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, then add pear juice and water (1 3/4 cups liquid all together).
Set in fridge until almost firm. Then whip with beater for about 1 minute.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix and cook until peanuts pop, add 1 1/2 teaspoon soda; beat and pour.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first six ingredients in a bowl, beat until smooth. Layer half of cooked macaroni in bottom of a greased 9 - inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with 1 2/3 c. cheese and layer remaining macaroni on top. Pour milk mixture over macaroni, sprinkle with breadcrumbs and remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered for 50 minutes. For cheesier macaroni, add 2 1/2 more cups of cheddar cheese. This recipe is enough for a meal by itself. Feeds 6-8 people.

title: tater fried chicken
directions: Combine egg, 2 tablespoons water and seasoned salt.
Dip chicken pieces into mixture, then roll in potato flakes.
Salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with oregano.
Melt butter or margarine in shallow baking pan and add the chicken pieces.
Bake in 375° oven about 1 hour or until all pieces are done.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Place cheese, bacon and onion in pie crust.
In mixing bowl, combine eggs, cream and mustard.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in filling comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch lengths with scissors, then saute until done. Add celery, onion and pepper.
Cook until done (vegetables will be soft). Now add soup, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and water. Simmer 10 minutes, then add shrimp and continue simmering 20 minutes.
Season with salt and serve with rice.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup, onion and cheese.
Then mix with potatoes.
Put in pan and top with crumbled corn flakes and 1/2 stick melted butter.
Cover and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder, vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Add apples and walnuts.
Mixture will be stiff.
Bake in a greased angel food cake pan at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool 10 to 20 minutes and invert on rack.

title: ice box pickles
directions: Bring mixture to a boil and pour over the cucumbers and onions in a gallon jar.
Refrigerate for at least 3 days before eating. Store pickles in the refrigerator until ready to use them.
Great with sandwiches.
Will keep well.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: frosty pineapple salad
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt in a large bowl, stirring well. Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended. Spoon into paper lined muffin cups. Cover and freeze up to 1 month.
Makes 20.

title: zucchini soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, saute the onions and zucchini in the olive oil or butter for about 10 minutes or until browned.
Add the chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Add the lima beans and peas.
When mixture comes to a boil again, reduce the heat and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until the vegetables are soft.
Add salt and pepper.
Puree all ingredients together in a blender. Return to saucepan; heat and serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: western meal in one
directions: Brown turkey in oil with garlic.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until onion is transparent; drain fat.
In 2-quart casserole, combine meat mixture, salt, chili powder, beans, tomatoes and rice.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Bake 15 minutes more.
(Can be microwaved.)

title: stuffed turkey drumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With a sharp knife, make one slit lengthwise in each drumstick.
Leaving outside skin intact, push meat back from bone.
With knife, remove bone and cartilage. Sprinkle inside of each boned drumstick lightly with salt and pepper.

title: italian speckled trout
directions: Marinate trout for 3 to 4 hours in Italian dressing in the refrigerator. Remove fillet and place in a deep pan (buttered). Add all spices according to taste. Add some olive oil. Pour in Italian dressing until it covers the trout. Bake fish at 350° until almost done, then remove and cover trout with cheese and sprinkle a few of the bread crumbs. Bake until cheese melts and fish is baked. Serves 2 people.

title: beef stew
directions: In crock-pot, add stew meat, sliced carrots, potatoes and onions.
Add 1 small bottle ketchup with equal amounts water, making sure potato-meat mixture is covered; may need to add more. Salt to taste.
Cook slowly for 4 to 6 hours.
Also may simmer on stove until meat is done and tender.

title: lena's doughnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat the eggs very well, gradually add sugar and continue beating.
Mix in shortening and buttermilk. Sift the dry ingredients together and stir them in.
Chill the dough, roll 1/3 inch thick.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reserve a little of the water to make a paste with Clear Jell.
Thicken with Clear Jell and cook until it is clear.
A small box of jello may be added for flavoring.

title: apple crunch
directions: Peel apples; slice thin.
Place in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, egg and spices until mixture looks like cornmeal.
Put on top of apples.
Add water.
Cut up margarine on top.
Cook in oven at 375° for 1 hour or until top is brown and crusty.

title: western lima barbecue
directions: Soak beans in 3 cups of water for 5 to 6 hours or overnight. Bring to a boil, then turn heat low and simmer 30 minutes, adding additional hot water if necessary.
Fry onion and garlic in oil until golden.
Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice, mustard, salt, Worcestershire and catsup.
Heat to boiling.
Place drained beans in baking dish.
Pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, adding hot bean juice as necessary.
Score wieners and press into sauce, spooning sauce over top.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Soften the gelatin in the 1/2 cup of skim milk.
Heat evaporated milk with sugar.
Add softened gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Slowly add lemon peel and juice to the cooled gelatin mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into ice cube trays and place in freezer.
When mixture is mushy, remove from the freezer and fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Return to freezer until firm, then remove.
Put in a chilled bowl and beat until fluffy.
Refreeze and serve.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Pour over sliced peaches in bowl; toss to coat peaches evenly.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry. Add peaches; dot with butter or margarine.
Adjust top crust; cut slits to allow steam to escape.
Bake in 425° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: kitty litter cake
directions: Prepare cake mixes and bake.
Prepare pudding and chill until ready to assemble.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix meat, onion, rice, crumbs, egg and seasonings in a bowl. Form into balls; place in a deep greased casserole and pour the diluted soup over them.
Bake 1 hour at 375°; cover partially ajar.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and mincemeat. Sift dry ingredients and stir into cream mixture.
Add pecans. Drop 1 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: review and herald cafeteria pot pie
directions: Scramble in 3 tablespoons margarine 1 egg and cook well.
Add onion, carrots and celery, stir over fire for a few minutes.
Add green peas, barely cover with water and cook until the vegetables are firmly tender.
Drain off the liquid and return it to the stove.
While it is coming to a boil, mix 1 tablespoon flour, 1 egg yolk and 1/4 cup cream.
Add the hot broth to the flour mixture, stir well and bring to a boil.
Add vegetable mixture.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix well, but lightly.
Bake at 350° for one hour in loaf pan.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce and onion mix.
Add 1/2 can of water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Boil noodles until done. Layer meat, noodles and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Cover with finely chopped nuts after rolling into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight, then serve with crackers or celery sticks.

title: ice cream soda
directions: Mix milk and chocolate syrup.
Add ice cream.
Pour in chilled club soda; stir quickly.

title: caramel for apples
directions: Melt together condensed milk and butterscotch chips.
Add cinnamon, vinegar and sprinkle of salt.
Dip slices of apple in the caramel.

title: kolache
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter, sugar and salt to cooled milk. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to milk mixture.
Add egg and flour until mixture is pliable.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Punch down.
Form into small biscuits. Place on greased cookie sheet; let rise.
With fingers, form hole in center.
Fill with prunes or favorite filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole(or pork chop casserole)
directions: Mix soup, soup mix, water and rice (not cooked).
Spray bottom of pan with Pam cooking spray.
Spread mixture in pan.
Put meat on top.
Season.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: skillet hofbrau hash
directions: In 12-inch skillet or electric skillet melt margarine and add brown sugar.
Stir in apples and onions.
Cook, uncovered, until almost tender (about 3 minutes).
Add potatoes, sauerkraut, sausage, poppy seed, salt and pepper and stir together.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: white chili
directions: Combine beans, broth, water, onion and garlic in Dutch oven. Add chicken, chilies, cumin, oregano and red pepper.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Spoon
into serving bowls; top each with cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until creamy.
Press in bottom of pie shell.
Cook sugar, flour, milk, oleo and beaten yolks until it thickens.
Cool and spread over peanut butter mixture.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put fruit in lemon flavored gelatin base for a good tasting salad.
Serve on crisp lettuce with a fluffy cream cheese dressing. It's good enough for a luncheon party.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops; put in big baking pan.
Parboil potatoes (peeled).
Put with pork chops.
Add carrots, peas and cut up tomatoes.
Add water; cover pan with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° until potatoes and carrots are soft, about 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: no cook strawberry jam
directions: Use only 1 pint size or less containers that have been sterilized with tight fitting lids.
While jars are draining, crush strawberries.
Add measured sugar and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix water and Sure-Jell in small saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute stirring constantly.
Stir into fruit immediately and continue stirring for 3 minutes.
Ladle quickly into jars and tightly seal the lids.
Let stand at room temperature several hours before storing in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 5 (8 ounce) containers.

title: killer brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat.
Stir often until melted.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Pat 1/2 of mixture into bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over cooked dough.
Pour caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: reba mcentire's broccoli casserole(celebrity recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Steam broccoli just until crisp; drain. Mix broccoli, soup, water chestnuts, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes,
until bubbling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate crumb crust for black bottom pie
directions: In small bowl, combine crumbs and cocoa; add margarine and stir until evenly blended.
Stir Equal in well.
Press mixture evenly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Makes one 9-inch pie crust. Calories per serving (without filling):
Serves 8. Diabetic exchanges per serving (without filling):
milk 0, vegetable 0, fruit 0, bread 1/2, meat 0 and fat 0.

title: never fail dill pickles
directions: Put dill heads, garlic buds, crushed red pepper and mustard seed in bottom of 1/2 gallon jar.
Pack whole cucumbers in jar (not brined).
Put alum on top of cucumbers.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Seal.
Do not double recipe.

title: copper pennies(diabetic)
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender; drain and cool. Add sliced onions and green peppers (sliced or diced).
Combine soup and remaining ingredients; pour over carrots, onions and peppers.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pie crust.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: fruit nut roll
directions: Mix well and sprinkle in cracker crumbs on waxed paper to keep from sticking.
Store in refrigerate overnight.
Slice.

title: scampi
directions: Heat butter in a skillet and fry shrimp about 5 minutes or until cooked, shaking pan over high heat.
Sprinkle shrimp with salt and pepper and place on a hot serving plate.
Add garlic and parsley to butter remaining in skillet.
Stir for 30 seconds and pour over shrimp.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: grandma ammons' pickled beans and corn
directions: String and break beans.
Boil corn on cob, then cut corn off cob.
Boil beans until tender and drain.
Put all beans and corn in a stone crock.
Add salt and mix well with beans and corn.
Add enough water to cover beans and corn.
Weight down with plate. Tie a clean cloth over top of crock.
Allow beans to work about 7 to 10 days.
Pack in hot jars to 1/2-inch from top and seal. Bring canner to 10 pounds pressure and remove from heat.
When pressure drops to zero, remove jars and store.

title: jello whip
directions: Use any flavor of jello.
Fix jello according to package directions.
Let chill until partially set.
Add Cool Whip and whip together.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: In a 10-inch glass pie plate, spread beans.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Serve with tortilla chips. Serves 8.

title: filling
directions: Boil 2 minutes.
Add 1 can coconut and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; make a well.
Add all liquids, eggs and pumpkin.
Add cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave tortilla pizza
directions: You will also need 2 paper towel sheets.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix breadcrumbs, milk, ground chuck, onions and egg.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Form into 1 inch balls and brown in small amount of oil; drain.
Combine butter, gingersnaps, brown sugar and pineapple juice.
