Simmer 30 minutes until thick and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Pour sauce over meatballs and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon into chafing dish over candle.
Put pineapple chunks, if desired.
Yields 30 to 40 meatballs.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in pan and use to spoon over tops of biscuits.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix the cream cheese, milk and sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Tear cake into pieces.
Layer cake with cheese mixture in a large bowl.
Mix strawberries with glaze and spread on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: steak and potato supper
directions: Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat the meat with flour mixture.
In skillet, brown meat slowly in hot oil.
This should take 20 to 30 minutes.
Add broth; cover lightly and simmer 30 minutes or until almost tender.
Add water, if needed.
Place potatoes and onions with salt and pepper. Cover tightly.
Cook slowly about 30 minutes, or until potatoes are done.
Sprinkle a little parsley on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: linzer tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 10-inch diameter spring-form pan.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Cook all other ingredients together until thick, being careful not to let it stick.
Remove from heat and pour in shell.
Spoon meringue onto hot pie, sealing edges to prevent shrinking.
Bake until delicate brown, about 10 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown meat; add 1 cup water or stock.
Add the rest of ingredients; simmer until celery is soft.
Serve on buns.

title: aunt ann's prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together; beat.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat well.
Mix all dry ingredients, except soda, together.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Alternate adding dry ingredients and buttermilk; mix well.
Add prunes and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Garnish with onions.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: punch pie
directions: In a bowl, beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
In another bowl, crush graham crackers; add baking powder and pecans.
Mix the dry ingredients with the stiff egg whites. Bake in a greased 9-inch pie pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with whipped cream and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: apple breakfast pie
directions: Combine Bisquick, egg, milk, sugar, vegetable oil, nuts and raisins in bowl.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch pan.
Top with apples.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and oleo.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: strawberry jelly with figs
directions: Mix sugar, Jell-O and mashed figs and cook 20 minutes or until it thickens.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In Dutch oven or large saucepan, heat oil and brown beef.
Add soup mix and paprika blended with tomatoes.
Simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Stir in flour and salt blended with water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions. To serve, arrange goulash over noodles.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken stock, chicken, celery, carrots and onion. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat, simmer 30 minutes.
Season to taste.
Add bouillon cubes.
Pour hot into hot jars leaving 1-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process pints 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Use whole chicken for making stock.
Yields 8 pints.

title: yummy munchies
directions: Spread crackers on a large baking dish with edges.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crackers.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 30 minutes, stirring once.
Makes 1 pound.

title: jen's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter together in large saucepan and heat, stirring together until smooth.
Do not let mixture boil! Add the sugar last.
So yummy.
So easy.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until tender.
Add to bread crumbs, then add giblet broth to moisten.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: cinnamon ice cream
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sugar and cinnamon in large saucepan for 15 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in cream and extract.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all but corn.
Then add corn; put in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: hot heavenly biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with flour until dough leaves the sides of bowl.
Knead dough on lightly floured board until smooth.
Roll dough out about 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: children's letter pretzels
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Add the honey and salt. Add the flour; knead.
Roll into "snakes."
Form snakes into letters on waxed paper.
Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle with salt.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: butter pecan ice cream dessert
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press evenly in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Beat pudding with milk, then add coconut and softened ice cream.
Spread over crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate; is better frozen.

title: elda's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape dough on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: grandma's best baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, remove bacon and saute in bacon grease. In casserole dish or cake pan add pork and beans, syrup, brown sugar, ketchup and mustard.
Add bacon, crumbled, onion and bacon grease.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bride's cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar. Add flour alternately with milk.
Beat after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake for 40 minutes or until cooked.

title: beef manana dinner
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir ground beef, onion, celery and green bell pepper over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Drain off grease.
Stir in soup, tomato sauce, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into casserole dish.
Top with plain cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: (topping) - or pineapple sauce
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add juice gradually to cornstarch in saucepan, making a smooth mixture. Cook.
Stir constantly until thickened and clear. Remove from heat.
Add pineapple. Add lemon or lime juice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Good on gingerbread or a sundae or for any topping.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer macaroni and cheese in a casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour milk on top and dot with the butter. Bake at 375° to 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the butter, eggs and sugar, then add the dry ingredients, then the nuts.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: one hour yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt, sugar and oil.
Add enough flour to make a
real
stiff dough.
Let stand about 15 minutes. Make out rolls.
Let
rise
to double in size.
Bake at 400°. Makes about 14 rolls.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; let rise 1 hour, then mix the milk, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour with the salt. Add to first mixture; knead well.
Raise to double in size.
Roll out; cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot fat.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or make a glaze.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine cream, butter, cheese, onions and mushrooms in top of large double boiler to melt and combine.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Layer noodles, crabmeat, then sauce in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marie's stuffed eggs
directions: Boil your eggs.
Cool and half.
Use yolks for something else or throw away.
Mix ingredients.
Stuff eggs.
Garnish with parsley (dried or fresh).

title: apple doughnuts
directions: Combine biscuit mix and sugar; add chopped apples, milk, vanilla, eggs and spices.
Stir until well blended.
Knead dough on a heavily floured board until smooth.
Roll out dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out doughnuts with a floured 3-inch doughnut cutter.
Drop doughnuts, a few at a time, into 400° oil about 2 inches deep in pan.
Cook about 1 minute on each side or until evenly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Bring apple juice and lemon to a boil.
Stir in confectioners sugar and beat until smooth.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons glaze over each doughnut while warm.
Roll half of glazed doughnuts in toasted or tinted coconut. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: green stuff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
At same time, heat soup and 2 cans of water over low-medium heat.
When broccoli is ready, drain and mix into the soup.
Add rice and Cheez Whiz to soup.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mere's broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Saute onion in butter.
Add drained mushrooms and broccoli.
Cook until broccoli is thawed.
Add soup and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Pour into prepared casserole dish and top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly.

title: crispy breaded tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes as desired thickness. Roll tomato slices in a milk and egg mixture. Make a mixture of flour and bread crumbs. Then roll the tomatoes in flour mixture. In a large skillet, heat butter. Add tomatoes and cook, covered, until brown. Uncover pan and turn tomatoes. (Add more butter, if needed.) Lay a piece of Mozzarella cheese over each tomato and cover pan. Cook until cheese is melted.

title: chicken fiesta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season chicken with pepper, salt and paprika.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken to skillet. Brown well.
Drain chicken on paper towels.
Set aside.
Cook sausage, celery and onions in same skillet over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add rice, corn, broccoli and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top of rice mix, pressing chicken slightly into rice mixture.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cover with foil.
Cook until chicken is no longer pink in center. Uncover.
Lightly brown cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, save broth to boil spaghetti in. Debone chicken and dice. Saut celery, bell pepper and onion. Combine all ingredients. If needed, add some of broth to thin mixture.

title: uncooked green tomato chow-chow
directions: Sprinkle layers of tomatoes, cabbage, onion and green pepper with salt; let stand overnight.
In the morning, squeeze vegetables dry.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into clean jars and cover.
Kept in refrigerator, relish will keep from 2 to 3 weeks. Makes about 1 quart.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients into blender.
Fill blender with ice and blend well until ice crushed and well blended.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil hen.
Debone and dice meat.
Take 3 1/2 quarts of broth and all other ingredients.
Simmer until done.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package and add to broth.
It thickens and absorbs broth as it sets.

title: barbecued country spareribs
directions: Combine the celery seed, chili powder, brown sugar and paprika. Cut the spareribs into serving pieces and rub with mixture.
Put into pan sprayed with Pam spray.
Cover with the tomato soup and vinegar. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: magic pumpkin pie(for weight watchers)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, adding a few at a time, until well mixed.
Put in pie pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or a knife comes out clean. Serves 4. Each serving:
1/2 protein, 1 milk, 3/4 bread and 1/2 vegetable.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Melt margarine, add Bisquick and sour cream.
Mix ingredients with wooden spoon.
Grease muffin tins.
Bake at 450°.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and rhubarb.
Set aside.
Blend butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add alternately to butter mixture with buttermilk.
Add rhubarb mixture, coconut, nuts and raisins and mix together.
Pour into a greased 7 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: never can cucumber pickles
directions: Mix salt with water.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 3 days; drain off salt water.
Rinse 3 times.
Add alum to pitcher of water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours; drain, leaving cucumbers in container.
Rinse 3 times.
Fill container of cucumbers with undiluted vinegar.
Let stand 7 days.
Drain off vinegar, but don't rinse.
Add 3 cups sugar, turmeric and enough pickling spice to form ball size of walnut; tie in a cloth and drop in container with cucumbers, sugar and turmeric (leave in container).
Add 3 cups sugar everyday for 3 days and serve when desired.

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Mix well. Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Chill 1 hour.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, mustard, lemon juice and onion.
Stir in shrimp.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: fruit jello salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions on package using liquids listed above.
Chill until syrupy.
Add fruit, making sure bananas are covered with liquid.
Serves 6.

title: peach cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, cinnamon, syrup and butter; mix well. Add flour, soda and peaches.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Can crumble bacon on top if you wish.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine soda, flour, sugar, salt and oil.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add carrots, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large microwavable bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.

title: frozen pepper cabbage
directions: Chop together cabbage, peppers and carrot.
Add salt; let set for 1 hour.
Then boil sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed. Cool this mixture before adding to cabbage, then put in container and freeze.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty blueberries into strainer.
Wash under cold running water.
Set aside to drain.
Pour oil into 8 or 9-inch cake pan; tilt to cover bottom.

Pour muffin mix, egg and water into pan; stir with a fork until blended (about 1 minute). Sprinkle drained blueberries, brown sugar and cinnamon over batter; use a fork to fold in batter just enough to create a marbled effect.
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes until coffee cake tests done with a toothpick.
Use a knife to loosen cake from sides.
Cut and serve directly from pan.

title: greek easter cookies
directions: Cream butter with Crisco.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix egg yolk and vanilla; add to mixture.
Add the evaporated milk.
Beat the egg whites to form a stiff peak.
Add to mixture.
Add in flour and baking powder a little at a time using your hands and knead together.
Let set for 1 hour.
Roll out dough into long strips and twist into braided shape.
Brush tops with beaten egg before baking and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: warm bleu cheese and garlic dip
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
After cream cheese has softened, beat in 1/2 cup of half and half, then add the Bleu cheese, garlic and chopped chives.
Mix with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious served with carrot sticks and broccoli flowerets.

title: haigagen kebab(armenian mystery package)
directions: You will need 4 large pieces of aluminum foil.

title: swiss spinach bake(low calorie)
directions: Cook spinach as label directs; drain well, squeezing out excess water.
In a 1-quart casserole dish, beat egg and stir in remaining ingredients.
Add spinach.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 minutes or until center is set.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice and soup.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top of chicken breasts. Pour the 2 cups of water around sides of dish.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnut
directions: Evening before party (24 hours):
Wrap 1/2 piece of bacon around each chestnut.
Use toothpick to secure bacon.
Bake in a cake pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drain grease.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all cheeses in food processor or using electric mixer until smooth.
Add onion, Worcestershire, paprika, chives and pepper.
Blend well.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans and parsley.
Chill until firm.
Serve with any type cracker.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook 1 hour in pressure cooker; mash with potato masher. Serve on hamburger buns with cole slaw.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir after 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Mix well and boil 1 minute.
Pour mixture over 2 gallons popped corn.
Toss and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: lemon rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg, lemon juice and rind.
Combine flour with baking powder, salt and crushed candy.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix at high speed with mixer until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until slightly brown.
Cool slightly before removing.
Frost, if desired.

title: excellent spinach
directions: Cook spinach; mix together with onion soup and sour cream. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Heat thoroughly and serve.
May add bread crumbs on top and 2 to 3 tablespoons melted butter drizzled over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: berry pickers' reward muffins
directions: Line 20 muffin cups with paper baking cups; set aside. In mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside. In large bowl, beat butter with electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add 1 1/4 cups sugar and mix on medium speed until combined. Beat in eggs, sour cream and vanilla until combined. With a spoon, stir dry ingredients into beaten mixture until just moistened. Fold in raspberries. Spoon into prepared muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.

title: waffles
directions: Mix liquid ingredients and stir into dry
mixture.
Bake in waffle iron until brown.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, Karo and butter to boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir until melted.
Mix in cornflakes.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Chill for two hours. Return to room temperature before serving.

title: 1860's muster day gingerbread cookies
directions: Heat the brown sugar, molasses, cinnamon, ginger and cloves to the boiling point.
Remove from heat, add the baking soda and pour over the butter in a large mixing bowl.
Stir until the butter has melted, then stir in the egg and flour thoroughly.
Knead the dough for a few minutes, then gather into a ball.
Refrigerate until firm enough to roll easily, about 30 minutes (if chilled longer, allow to warm to rolling consistency).
Roll on a slightly floured board and cut with fancy cookie cutters.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet in a preheated oven at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa, and all to the mixture.
Add salt and flour with the buttermilk and flavorings.
Alternately, add soda and vinegar, do not beat too hard, just blend.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Makes two layers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain. Add onion soup mix, sour cream and 2/3 of grated cheese.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into baking dish. Cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbling. Cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Melt the chocolate bar on low heat.
Mix peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Dip out into small piles.
Let cool and eat.

title: dilled mushrooms
directions: Drain liquid from mushrooms into a 1-cup measure for next step.
Place mushrooms in a small bowl; sprinkle with dill weed. Measure 1/2 cup of the mushroom liquid into a small saucepan. Stir in vinegar and sugar.
Heat just to boiling; pour over mushrooms.
Chill at least one hour to season.

title: 100% parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Dip chicken in butter; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise. Lay crescent roll flat and bake.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of roll when done and cooled. Take chopped vegetables and sprinkle on top of mixture.
Last layer is grated cheese.

title: easy chocolate chip cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. With mixer, beat cheese until smooth and fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Toss morsels with flour; stir into cheese mixture. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Bake 35 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched. Cool and top with glaze. Serve chilled. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pickled okra
directions: Use wide-mouth pint jars, 1/2 pound okra per jar.
Use fresh okra, about 2 inches long.
Leave 1/2 inch stem on.
Place in sterilized jars.
Add 1 clove garlic, 1 hot pepper, 1 teaspoon celery salt and 1 teaspoon mustard to each jar.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Pour hot solution over okra and seal.

title: biscotti di mamma("s" cookies)
directions: You may add flavoring:
anise, almond, etc.

title: meat loaf w t c
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Ideally use a loaf pan smaller than the standard size.
Use pan (Pyrex) approximately 2 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch.
Put meat into large mixing bowl.
Heat butter in a small skillet and add the onion and green pepper.
Cook, stirring, until wilted.
Add the mushrooms and cook until wilted.
Add the drained pimento.
When the mushrooms give up their liquid, continue cooking until the liquid evaporates.
Add the mixture to the meat, add the cream, egg, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pack into loaf pan and smooth over.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and let rest for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6. Good with scalloped potatoes.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown hamburger, ham, pepperoni and sausage. Drain and add spaghetti sauce. Simmer 30 minutes. Make bread dough according to box instructions. Roll out dough and place on a cookie sheet. Pour meat mixture onto 1/2 of dough. Sprinkle with cheese. Fold dough over and seal edges. Bake at 350 for approximately 30 minutes or until bread is golden brown. Makes 2 stromboli.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Fix jello according to package directions.
Add blueberries, pineapple and chopped pecans to jello.
Put in refrigerator to jell.
Smooth Cool Whip on top.
You can add any type of fruit, fresh or canned, to the jello.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 of the cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mother johnson's date pie
directions: Stew dates with enough milk to cover.
Put through a colander or use a blender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake as a custard pie in an uncooked shell.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water, real good.
Then add water. Mix just enough for dough to evenly absorb water.
Mold into ball and place on well-floured surface.
Roll out to pie-plate size. Lift carefully to avoid stretching dough and place in pie plate. Trim around edges with dinner knife.
(For pie with top crust, recipe should be doubled.)
Add filling, moisten around edge with water, then place top crust over filling and crimp around edges with fork tines.
Then bake according to pie directions.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Continue beating slowly, adding sugar until dissolved.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil-lined cookie sheet.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Set aside. Combine softened butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water. Beat until creamy.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage topped potato casserole
directions: Combine soup, cheese, sour cream and milk.
Place one-half of the potatoes in a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Repeat layers; brown link sausage in skillet. Drain; cut each in half.
Arrange sausage pieces on top of casserole and bake an additional 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: franks florentine
directions: Spread spinach in bottom of 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Combine rice, soup, onion and milk; spoon over spinach.
Score half franks with an X-shaped cut; arrange on casserole, pressing into rice. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple and 1/2 cup pecans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.
Serves 40.
Recipe can be cut in half for smaller groups.

title: florida cake
directions: Make Jell-O as directed and refrigerate until syrupy or slightly set.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with layer of coconut bars, breaking anywhere needed to fill in.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy with butter, then add sugar.
Blend in drained pineapple. Spread half on the coconut bars.
Spread another layer of bars and cover with the other half of the cream cheese, butter and pineapple mixture.
Beat syrupy Jell-O on high speed for 10 minutes until frothy.
Spread on top of other ingredients.
Let set.
Then top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Let set 24 hours.

title: jam up good cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add egg and oil, beating until well blended.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20-30 minutes or until done and golden brown.

title: cold mostaccioli salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar.
Cool.
Add all other ingredients to mostaccioli.
Serve cold.

title: transparent pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour, salt and melted butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue cooking until done.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix and stir over medium heat.
Cook until it forms a firm ball when tested in water.
Spread on your desired cake.

title: marshmallow lime salad
directions: Melt jello, cream cheese and marshmallows in hot water on stove and let cool.
Add other ingredients and let congeal. Serves 12.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Place in baking dish pats of butter.
Cover with onion slices, then cover with Minute rice.
Place chicken, seasoned with salt and pepper on top of rice.
Brush with Kitchen Bouquet.
Mix soup, parsley, seasoning and water.
Mix well and spoon over chicken. Cover and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 400°.

title: spicy southwestern beef stew
directions: Place beans in heavy medium saucepan with enough cold water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain beans.
Place beef in large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons Santa Fe Seasoning over; toss well.
Add flour and toss to coat.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, eggs, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Press into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Unmold on rack of broiler pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerated mashed potatoes
directions: Add all ingredients to mashed potatoes until fluffy.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased, 2-quart casserole, uncovered. After it is baked, you can place in refrigerator for as long as 2 weeks and use what you need.
Need to bake for 45 minutes then or microwave until heated through.

title: mexican appetizers
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, make a layer of rat cheese, then jalapenos and another layer of rat cheese.
Mix eggs, flour and milk; pour over layers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool before serving.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Break eggs in large bowl.
Beat slightly with fork.
Add milk, pepper, salt and bread.
Beat until bread has disintegrated.
Add onion, cheese and ground beef.
Mix well.
Pack this mixture in a loaf pan.
Combine sugar, ketchup and mustard.
Spread this over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: salmon en croute with herb butter
directions: Place salmon fillets, wine and water in 10-inch skillet. Cover and cook over low heat about 10 minutes until fish flakes easily from fork.
Drain and cool.	Saut green onions in butter in 10-inch skillet.
Stir in mushrooms and salt; cook about 5 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Stir in cream cheese until well blended. Remove from heat.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Blend the cream cheese and sour cream in a small bowl and set aside.
Mash potatoes thoroughly until smooth.
Add cream cheese mixture and beat well.
Stir in chives, salt and pepper.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
At this point potatoes may be covered and refrigerated.
One hour before serving, dot with butter, and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Makes 8 to 14 servings.

title: hawaiian crock-pot chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Combine rest of ingredients while chicken is baking and cook until thick and glossy.
Put baked chicken in crock-pot and pour sauce over it.
Cook on high for 3 hours or low for 5 hours.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Bring to boil tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
In skillet, cook ground chuck and onion until done; drain.
Add to tomatoes; let cook for 5 minutes.
Then add macaroni.
Cook on medium heat until macaroni is tender.
(Good with cornbread.)

title: patrick's punch
directions: Stir in bowl to soften the sherbet.
Stir in the limeade concentrate, the ginger ale and water.
Pour into glasses to serve.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° in an 8 x 12-inch pan for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Wash rice thoroughly.
Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into small balls.
Heat tomato soup and water in cooker.
Drop meatballs in soup mixture.
Close cover securely. Cook 10 minutes with pressure regulator rocking slowly.
Let pressure drop of its own accord.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift
together	the
dry ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in a bowl.
Add dry ingredients and oleo. Mix
only until flour is moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a well-greased 9
x
5-inch
loaf	pan
for 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted
in
center comes out clean.
Cool 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: mornay sauce
directions: Bring milk, onion and bay leaf to a full boil.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Strain.
Over low heat, melt butter in saucepan; add flour and cook until light brown.
Gradually add milk and cream, stirring constantly, until mixture starts to boil.
Stir in salt and pepper to taste.

title: nancy's "too easy pie"
directions: Stir together and pour into shell.
Freeze covered.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients in order given. Beat at medium speed 1 minute.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: taco casserole
directions: Lay in layers the meat, onion, beans, chips and cheese in that order.
Make a mixture of soup and tomatoes.
Pour over casserole. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: good cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, oil, brown sugar and granulated sugar. Add egg, Special K, oatmeal, coconut, salt, soda, flour and vanilla.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork slightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: party dip
directions: Pour over chopped ingredients and mix.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: four layer chocolate pie
directions: Mix butter with flour.
Add nuts.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: quick quesadillas
directions: Place tortilla on microwavable plate. Arrange Singles, cut diagonally, on tortilla. Fold tortilla in half. Cover. Microwave on High 25 to 40 seconds or until cheese melts. Let stand, covered, until cool. Fold in half again. Makes 1 serving.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add lemon juice and tomato juice. Cool until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set several hours. Serve on greens.
Serves 15.

title: double marble cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Prepare cake batters according to directions.
Stir 1/2 cup chocolate chips into chocolate batter.
Spoon vanilla and chocolate into pan and swirl.
Bake 33 to 38 minutes.
Check with a toothpick.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Gently spread Marshmallow Creme over warm cake.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt the remaining chocolate chips and swirl through the Marshmallow Creme.

title: linda's sunday chicken
directions: Mix and heat soups, milk, rice and 1/2 of dry soup mix. Butter 9 x 13 baking pan or dish and pour mixture into pan.
Place chicken on top and sprinkle with remaining dry soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours 15 minutes.
Do not peek.
Bake while at church - come home and fix vegetables to go with your chicken - tastes great.

title: luscious chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter (oleo), crumbs and sugar; press on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken polynesia
directions: Place the Shake 'n Bake and Jell-O in the shaker bag and shake to blend.
Coat the chicken pieces with the Shake 'n Bake and Jell-O mix as directed on the envelope.
Place chicken in 9 x 2 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: hot pot calico
directions: Do not drain beans.
Mix all together, place in a baking dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix well.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool; then roll in powdered sugar.
This is a candy-like cookie.

title: poor man pizza
directions: On cookie sheet, place bread.
Place in order on bread, cheese, tomato, 1 ring from onion slice, cut bacon strip in half and place 2 halves on top.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Place on top rack in oven and bake at 400° until bread is golden and cheese is melted slightly.
Remove and let cool 3 minutes.

title: overnite cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage.
Put in refrigerator to keep crisp.
Chop other vegetables fairly fine.
Put in with crisp cabbage.
Add other 7 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables. Mix well.
This salad keeps several days.

title: powdered sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time, beating well until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk; add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan about 70 minutes at 325°.

title: no-fat split pea soup(serves 4)
directions: Soak split peas overnight in cold water.
Drain and rinse. Put in kettle and add water.
Bring to boil and then turn down to simmer.
Add all other ingredients except potatoes.
Set timer for 1 hour and 15 minutes, letting soup simmer for this time. When time is up, add in instant potatoes; stir and remove from heat.
Done!

title: peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Crush cookies and blend with margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Chill.

title: beer baked beans
directions: Brown sausage, breaking up, and saute onion in the same pan. Drain and crumble into large bowl. Add all the beans, brown sugar, barbecue sauce, mustard and beer.
Pour into bean pot or casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 300° for 4 to 5 hours, checking for moisture content by 3 1/2 hours.
(You can always stir in more beer if beans are too dry.)

title: tropical punch cooler
directions: Pour Hawaiian Punch, pineapple juice and orange juice into punch bowl.
Stir.
Add plenty of ice cubes.
Scoop in orange sherbet with small ball scooper.
Drink and enjoy!

title: fettucine with pesto sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain.
In a food processor or blender, process remaining ingredients until well blended.
(Sauce thins out on hot pasta.)
Toss pasta with sauce until well coated. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chocolate butter gooey bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg in a bowl, mixing well.
Press in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch glass baking dish.
Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar in a bowl until light.
Add the two remaining eggs and mix well. Spread over the chocolate cake mix layer.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels and bake for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes 12 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Make a paste of cocoa and food
coloring;
add
to
creamed
mixture.
Sift salt and flour and add to creamed mixture, alternating with the buttermilk.
Add vanilla,
soda and vinegar; blend in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in layer pans.
Cool and split layers to ice.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and pack tightly into quarter jar.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling hot mixture over the eggs and seal.
Eggs will be ready in 4 to 5 days.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cooked peanut butter icing
directions: Put all ingredients in heavy skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until right consistency to spread on cake.
Ice 3 layer cake, either yellow or devil's food.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Place into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheater cheesecake
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese and sugar.
In another bowl, add jello and water.
Add jello to milk.
Add cream cheese and sugar together with everything else.
Spread in pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: crumb cookies
directions: Mix almonds, flour, sugar, lemon peel and salt.
Cut butter or margarine into the mixture.
Add lemon juice and brandy or water; mix.
Spread on a greased pizza pan.
Do not press.

title: chestnut appetizers
directions: Wrap chestnuts with bacon which has been cut into thirds. Secure with toothpick. Bake for 1 hour at 275° in a glass dish. Drain grease from bacon.
Pour sauce over chestnuts and bake for 1 hour at 275°.

title: creamed green beans and potatoes
directions: Drain green beans, potatoes and mushrooms.
Cut potatoes into chunks.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour.
Blend in milk, basil, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vegetables; heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Put in a shallow pan for marinade. Combine oil, parsley, lemon juice, onion, mustard, salt and dash of pepper.
Pour over fish.
Marinate covered in refrigerator 6 hours. Drain, reserving marinade.
Place fish in well-greased wire grill basket.
Grill over medium coals 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Brush with marinade and grill 8 to 10 minutes more.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in casserole dish for 3 hours at 300°.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss lettuce, tomatoes, onion, beans and cheese together. Toss in salad dressing and Fritos when ready to serve.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Add dry cake mix, 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
(If mixer is used, add last 1/3 of cake mix by hand.)
Cover and chill 30 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off pepper tops and clean.
Boil 5 minutes.
Mix gravy mix and drained tomatoes.
Add beef and rice to mixture.
Fill peppers and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix flour, sugar and pineapple juice; mix in beaten eggs and pineapple.
Bake in 350° oven until set.
Sprinkle grated cheese and buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Return to oven to brown. Serve.

title: baked rice
directions: Cook rice in salt water until soft.
Place in a glass baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over rice.
Bake at 325° until liquid is baked into the rice.
About 1 hour.

title: balsamic grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and dip chicken in marinade.
Arrange in glass pans.
Pour remaining marinade over.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Grill, basting with marinade.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain; mash until fine.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Dump crushed pineapple into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan and spread evenly; do not drain.
Dump blueberry pie filling. Spread evenly over pineapple. Dump yellow cake mix (dry; do not add eggs, water, etc.) over blueberry filling, spreading evenly. Spread pecans over cake mixture evenly.
Slice butter or margarine into pats and place on top. Bake 1 hour in oven preheated to 350°.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla; mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion until a light brown.
Drain.
Put beef in casserole dish.
Mix soups and the milk and water.
Pour over beef and put potato tarts on top.
Cook about 30 minutes or until done.

title: brunswick stew(family sized version)
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in chicken broth, chicken, tomatoes, beans, corn and crushed red pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes.
Add okra; simmer an additional 5 minutes or until okra is tender.
In small jar with tight fitting lid, add flour to cold water; shake well.
Stir into stew mixture.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring frequently.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Yields 6 servings; each serving contains 300 calories.

title: chocolate fried pies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Roll out pie dough thinly and cut in rounds the size of a saucer.
Place one tablespoon cocoa mixture in center of pastry; top with small pats of butter.
Fold in half and crimp edges together with fork dipped in cold water to seal.
Fry one side at a time in vegetable oil until golden brown. Makes about 6 pies.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken; take off bone and cut in small pieces.
Saute onion and celery.
Place chicken and uncooked rice in casserole dish.
Mix both soups, 2 cans of broth (when chicken is cooked) with onions and celery.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for about an hour.
